title: homemade lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles in 6 quarts boiling water to which has been added 2 tablespoons salt.
Cook rapidly for 15 minutes.
Stir gently.
Remove from heat and drain.
Pour cold water over to cool.
Cook hamburger in heavy saucepan until color changes.
Add onions, garlic, tomato paste, water and salt.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Start with a layer of noodles, then Mozzarella cheese, then cottage cheese, then meat sauce.
Continue layering in that order until all is used up.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed cabbage roll
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling salted water a few minutes to soften; drain.
Combine beef, rice, onion, egg, salt and pepper with 2 tablespoons soup.
Divide meat mixture among cabbage leaves.
Roll and secure with toothpicks.
Place cabbage rolls in skillet and pour remaining soup over them.
Cover, cook over low heat about 40 minutes, stirring often, spoon sauce over.
Serves 4.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain Mandarin oranges and crushed pineapple.
Combine sour cream, fruit, marshmallows and coconut.
Refrigerate in serving bowl.
Decorate with cherries just before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in boiling water; add cold water.
Cool, then add remaining ingredients.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Mix altogether; mix like pie dough.
Spoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, marshmallows, cream cheese and water together. Refrigerate to thicken.
Fold in thawed strawberries and pour into mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: marinated vegetable potpourri
directions: Combine all vegetables in large salad bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in jar with tight fitting lid.
Shake well and pour over vegetables.
Marinate 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Makes 8 cups.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press equal portions onto bottoms of 24 lightly greased * or paper cup-lined muffin cups.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon equal amounts of mixture (about 3 tablespoons) into prepared cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with filling.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: black beans
directions: Pre-cooking instructions:
Rinse the beans; soak in 12 cups of water the night before.
In the same water, cook them for 20 minutes in the pressure cooker on medium heat with one whole onion, 1/2 of the green pepper and 2 teaspoons of salt.
After the beans have softened, remove the whole onion and the green pepper. In a frying pan, heat the 1/2 cup olive oil.
Add the onion (chopped) the garlic (mashed), cumin and the other half of the pepper (slices).
Cook until the onion and garlic are crystal.

title: banana bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Place oven rack in lowest position.
Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottoms only of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix sugar and margarine in large bowl.
Stir in eggs until well blended.
Add bananas, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients except nuts just until moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaves from pans; remove from pans.
Cool completely before slicing.
Wrap tightly and store at room temperature up to four days or refrigerate for up to 10 days.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Blend a sauce with mayo, little lemon juice and sugar.
Blend into salad.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix and press graham cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar in bottom of a casserole dish.
Slice bananas over this.
Mix milk and lemon juice; pour over bananas.
Spread pineapple over this. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut; top with cherries. Refrigerate.

title: mock angel food cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder four times.
Add boiled milk.
Mix well.
Add egg whites and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into layer pans.
Makes three thick layers or four thin layers. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Place banana slices between layers and ice with caramel icing.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Parkay.
Add amount of pecans that you want and drop on cookie sheet.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Brown sausage and drain fat.
Combine rice, sausage and rest of ingredients.
Put into a 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with banana, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts. Pour into well-greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Slice when cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cake:
In a 9-inch round pan, make cake.
Split it into 4 layers with dental floss.

title: glorified chicken
directions: Combine chicken, soup and sour cream.
Place in a shallow baking dish (buttered).

title: rigatoni with ham sauce
directions: Heat the olive oil in a large skillet.
Add the garlic and ham; saute over moderate heat until the garlic is lightly browned, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes with their juice and the pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Cook the pasta and toss with the sauce.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add all ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours or until tender.
Stir occasionally. Makes 6 servings.

title: turnips au gratin
directions: Cook diced turnips until almost tender, about 5 minutes. Drain well. Melt 1/4 cup butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once. Cook quickly, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat and add cheese, stirring until completely melted. Stir in cooked turnips. Turn into 10 x 6 x 2 baking dish. Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle on top of turnip mixture. Bake at 375° until crumbs are golden brown, about 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and bananas.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir until well mixed and pour into well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 mini loaves or 2 (8-inch) loaves.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring broth to boil and add peas, corn, and meat.
Add salt and pepper.
Add beaten eggs all at once while stirring thoroughly.

Wait for soup to be boiled again then pour cornstarch mixture very slowly, stirring constantly until broth thickens. Sprinkle fresh mushrooms and green onions on top, stirring and pour immediately into sour tureen.
Serve.

title: cappuccino caramels
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil, extending the foil over edges of pan.
Butter the foil; set the pan aside.
In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, melt the margarine or butter over low heat.
Stir in the brown sugar, sweetened condensed milk, corn syrup and coffee crystals.
Carefully clip a candy thermometer to the side of the pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the thermometer registers 248° or candy reaches firm-ball stage.
The mixture should boil at a moderate, steady rate over the entire surface.
Reaching firm-ball stage should take 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove the saucepan from the heat. Remove the candy thermometer from the saucepan.
Immediately stir in walnuts, vanilla and orange peel.

Quickly pour the caramel mixture into the prepared baking pan, smoothing the surface; cool. When caramel is firm, use the foil to lift it out of the pan. Use a buttered knife to cut the caramel into squares.
Wrap each caramel square in plastic wrap.
Or, place caramel squares in candy cups; arrange in a bowl lined with plastic wrap or cellophane or in a tin.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Pour dressing over warm potatoes.
Chill 2 hours.
Add celery, onion, chopped egg whites and sieved yolks.
Mix with mayo, sour cream and mustard.
Fold into salad.
Add salt to taste.
Chill two hours.

title: cheesy meat pie
directions: In skillet, melt butter; add beef and onion.
Brown well. Drain.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Spread mixture over pie crust.
Spread cheese over beef mixture.
Add milk, eggs and Worcestershire sauce to blender, then pour over meat and cheese. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: chocolate-peanut butter bars
directions: Cream peanut butter and margarine in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Stir in flour, salt and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until edges begin to brown.
Top with remaining 1 cup chocolate chips. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Spread melted chocolate over top.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Yields 18 servings.

title: quick hamburger meal
directions: On strip of foil, place hamburger patty, string beans and potato in that order.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Close foil tightly.
Place in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and spread with a small spatula in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Blend next 4 ingredients well and pour on top of cake mixture.
Be sure to spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: country pineapple casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in pineapple and lemon juice.
Fold in the bread cubes.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: baked pineapple chicken
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Mix juice with corn starch, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Place chicken, skin side up in shallow baking dish.
Broil till brown.
Pour sauce over chicken. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Place lemon and pineapple slices around chicken.
Spoon sauce from pan over all.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: 5 bean salad
directions: Mix celery, green pepper, salad oil, onion, sugar and vinegar. Drain beans; put in a bowl and pour first mixture over them. Chill overnight.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper in the butter. Blend in and cook until bubbly the flour, paprika, dash of pepper, salt and dry mustard. Remove from heat. Add the milk gradually. Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add the corn and egg.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in dish.
Mix with all other ingredients, except butter and corn flakes.
Put crushed corn flakes over top and drizzle with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: alcohol-free bloody mary mix
directions: In container of electric blender, combine tomato juice, horseradish, salad dressing mix, Worcestershire sauce, dill weed, garlic, oregano, hot sauce and black pepper. Blend until all ingredients are combined. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops; cut into bite size pieces.
Drain grease from skillet; saute onions.
Add Worcestershire sauce and pork chops, stirring constantly.
Add cooked rice and more Worcestershire sauce, stirring constantly until all rice is brown in color.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Melt butter and pour over pecans.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Mix garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce and stir into pecans.
Heat oven to 325°.
Bake approximately 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, vanilla, apples, and nuts (optional).
Bake at 325° for approximately 80 minutes or when toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 bread pan loaves.

title: caramel bundt rolls
directions: Lightly grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom.
Put in rolls and sprinkle with pudding mix.
Melt margarine; add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls and let rise in cool oven overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: patty's bestest chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Steam spinach for 4 minutes; drain well. Set aside to cool. Flatten each chicken breast 1/4-inch. Place 1/4 of the steamed spinach on each chicken breast; spread out to cover the surface of each breast. Place 1/4 of the Feta cheese on top of the spinach; spread out also. Roll up the chicken breasts; secure with toothpicks. Use as many as you need to keep all of the spinach and cheese inside. (Warn your guests of the toothpicks when serving.) Place rolled chicken breasts in a covered baking dish. Add mushroom soup and fresh mushrooms, cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: copper pennies
directions: Boil carrots until tender; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Keeps well.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat. Drain and set aside. Stir mayonnaise, milk, eggs, cornstarch, cheese, onions and pepper into meat. Turn into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 5 to 7.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on cookie sheet.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, shredded cheese, onion and black olives.

title: italian delight
directions: Cook hamburger, drain off grease.
In another skillet cook bell peppers, onions, and garlic (cook slowly) until done but not brown. Put in drained hamburger and add tomato sauce let simmer for 5 or 10 minutes.
Cook noodles, drain well.
Put noodles in large pan put hamburger mixture over them and stir well and put grated cheese on top.
Bake in oven just long enough to melt cheese.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add flour.
Whip egg yolks and add lemon, milk and whipped (stiff) egg whites.
Put in unbaked crust. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: tammi's whoopie pies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg; blend together well.
Add alternately milk and dry ingredients. Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 or 8 minutes in a 425° oven.
Cool on rack.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add with buttermilk to the flour and shortening mixture.
Mix well.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in butter, then remove.
Add chopped onion and chopped pepper to skillet and saute.
Return steak, tomatoes and beef bouillon cube.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients with water and soy sauce.
Add to steak and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: banana shake
directions: Combine in electric mixer and mix until fluffy.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In large saucepan, cook sugar, milk and salt until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Combine 1 cup flour with sugar and add Wesson oil.
Heat until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1 tablespoon lukewarm water.
Add remaining flour and mix.
Pinch out into rolls.
Let set 1 hour and bake at 400°.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Combine butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, sour cream, rum and almond extract, mixing well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with mashed bananas, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done. If loaf gets too brown, cover with foil.
Remove from pan; cool. Sprinkle sugar.

title: microwave candy bar fudge
directions: Line 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil, extending over edges; set aside.
Microwave margarine on 100% power for 1 to 2 minutes or until melted. Stir in cocoa, sugar and milk.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil, stirring once.
Stir again.
Cook for 1 minute more.
Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread in pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender and drain.
Mix together sour cream and chicken soup.
Simmer onion in margarine.
Combine all ingredients and place in casserole.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm crumbs.
Cook at 350° until it bubbles.

title: pork chops italian
directions: Pocket pork chops; stuff with Provolone cheese, and seal with toothpicks.
Mix eggs and milk.
Dip pork chops in the liquid, then dip in mixture of bread crumbs, basil and garlic until coated.
Place on baking rack.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Gradually add milk and blend well.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Blend 1/2 cup of hot mixture into egg yolks and add to hot mixture in saucepan.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly. Blend in butter, vanilla and coconut.
Cover and cool to lukewarm, stirring occasionally.
Pour into baked pastry shell. Top with meringue.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over washed rice.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes; drain.
Place wild rice in 2-quart casserole.
Add soup, mushrooms with liquid, water, seasonings and paprika.
Mix gently and let stand for a few minutes.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream together butter and shortening, then add cream cheese and sugar; beat until fluffy. Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: potato pizza
directions: Brown hamburger.
Place in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Top with a layer of thinly sliced onion and potatoes.
Mix soup and milk; pour over meat, potato and onion mixture.
Mix tomato sauce with sugar, oregano and salt and pepper.
Pour over soup mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Uncover and top with Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Cook chicken in seasoned water (enough for 1 1/2 quarts broth).
Cool in broth, debone and cut in large pieces.
Strain and save broth.
Chop peppers and onions.
Saute in oleo; add mushrooms, then Ro-Tel, cheese, Worcestershire, dry mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook vermicelli in chicken stock, strain and carefully combine all ingredients.
Add water chestnuts.
Fills 2 large casseroles.
Serves 12 to 14.
Freezes well.
Cook when thawed at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: best brownies by richard
directions: Combine in a small saucepan sugar, water and butter.
Boil and remove from heat.
Put 6 ounces of chocolate in saucepan.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts and rest of chocolate.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9-inch square pan.

title: carrots royale
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook carrots, covered in 1/2-inch boiling water, for 8 minutes. Drain. Turn carrots into a 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in raisins, Imperial, honey, lemon juice and ginger.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes, stirring occasionally. Spoon into serving bowl. Sprinkle with almonds. Serves 4.

title: gouda and crescent roll appetizer
directions: Cover Gouda on top and sides with mustard.
Place Gouda on flat crescent rolls (seal perforations using 4 crescents).
Pull up corners and side of crescent and seal on top securely by twisting the dough.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve right away.

title: indian bread
directions: Take 1 cup of cornmeal and 1 cup of flour.
Then mix it up with milk.
Put cooking oil in the pan.
Pour the mix in the pan and you cook it until it gets good and brown on the other side and then you turn it over.
You turn it with a spatula.
Then you eat it.
What makes it really good is to eat it with butter.

title: jarlsberg cod(jarlsberg torsk)
directions: Thaw fish.
Bring to boil enough water to cover fish; add 1 teaspoon salt per quart of water used.
Put fish in water and bring to a boil.
Remove from burner and let set until ready to eat.
Serve with drawn butter.
Tastes like lobster.

title: hot sausage appetizers
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix with hands; will be very sticky.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, cooking oil and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla, sour cream and zucchini; mix well. Sift dry ingredients together; add to sugar-egg mixture. Mix thoroughly. Pour into greased 8 x 11-inch pan. Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: any-day skillet
directions: Brown beef and drain off grease.
Add rice, salt, pepper, frozen vegetables and water.
Sprinkle dry soup over all; mix everything together.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: beans, beans, beans!
directions: Brown sausage, onions and celery.
Add dry mustard, brown sugar, tomato paste and soup.
Simmer about 1/2 hour.
Add all beans (do not drain).
Mix and bake 1 hour at 350° in large, covered pan or casserole dish.

title: tomato and blue cheese soup
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.
Spread the tomatoes in a shallow baking dish with the garlic.
Add seasoning to taste and bake for about 35 minutes.
Heat the oil in a large saucepan.
Add the leek and carrot and season lightly with salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until softened.
Stir in the stock and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil, then lower the heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add the blue cheese, cream and basil.
Transfer to a food processor or blender and process until smooth, working in batches if necessary.
Reheat the soup, but do not boil.
Ladle into bowls and garnish with the crumbled bacon and basil.

title: puffy baked german pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat 2 (9-inch) cast-iron skillets or heavy cake pans.
(You need sturdy pans that can hold and conduct heat.)
Mix the flour, sugar and salt.
Add milk and eggs, blending only until well combined, scraping down the sides of the bowl with a spatula.
Take the pans from the oven.
In each, put 2 tablespoons butter; swirl to coat with butter as it melts.

title: chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the oleo and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until fluffy. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in nuts, if desired.
Spread in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over cake.
Return to oven 2 to 3 minutes.
Using a knife dipped in water, spread the melted marshmallows evenly over cake.
Cool!

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Add oil to bottom of pizza pan.
Brush olive oil on pizza crust, then add toasted sesame seed and garlic powder; sprinkle on crust.
Just put the sesame seed around the outside of the pizza dough.
Add sauce to top of pizza crust and add Mozzarella cheese (part skim) on top of sauce.
Bake in oven just until the pizza dough is baked, about 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: summer sausage
directions: Can use venison or pork instead of ground beef.
I use less salt.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak
poppy
seed
in
milk.
Cream
the shortening and sugar. Add eggs.	Add
poppy seed mixture to buttermilk, then add soda, salt
and
flavorings
to
buttermilk mixture.
Add flour and milk-buttermilk
mixture
alternately to shortening mixture.
Bake in a
greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours at	350°.
Cool
in
the
pan for 10 minutes. Turn out and top with glaze, if desired.

title: glass bowl salad
directions: Break lettuce up into glass bowl.
Top with water chestnuts, then peas, then green onions.
Crumble bacon onto top.
Then boiled eggs.
Top with Ranch Style dressing.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: french country-style beef stew
directions: Combine meat and flour in a plastic bag.
Toss to coat evenly. In a 6 quart pot, brown meat in oil.
Add salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
Add remaining ingredients except mustard. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour or until beef is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Blend in mustard.
If too thin, add a little Wondra flour to thicken.
Serve over rice.

title: clay
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Sprinkle with water and mix carefully. Work in enough additional water with hands to make mixture of clay consistency.
Can add food coloring.
Mold into shapes.

title: thanksgiving cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry cake mix and spices in bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 10-inch buttered baking dish.
Top with topping and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Spread meat across bottom and up sides of a 10-inch pie pan. Mix remaining ingredients, except soup and cheese.
Fill meat shell with mixture
and
spread
soup
over all.
Bake 45 minutes. cut cheese in
strips.
Arrange on top and return to oven 5 or 6 minutes,
until
cheese is melted.
Garnish with a few slices of olives.
Slice and serve.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix carrots, oil, eggs and sugar; add dry ingredients (sifted together).
Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased, floured 9 X 13 pan for 40 minutes at 325°.
(2 loaf pans for 30 minutes)

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 9 x 13 inch pan.
Pour in cherry pie filling and pour in pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix on filling.
Top with nuts.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: southern coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites from the 4 eggs.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into 2 pie crusts and bake in oven at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Make a dough from flour and water.
Add sugar, honey, cinnamon and raisins.
Bake for 1 hour.
Spread icing on top.
Eat while hot.
Delicious!

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Clean and cut up chicken; boil in water until done.
Cool and bone chicken and cut into small bite-sized pieces.
Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Thin the soup with 1/2 can of chicken broth.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Make up the stuffing mix according to directions, except use chicken broth instead of water and butter.
Put stuffing on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: paskha with custard base
directions: In top of double boiler, blend cream, sugar and egg yolks. Cook over simmering water, stirring until sugar is dissolved and sauce coats a metal spoon (about 15 minutes).
Remove from heat and let cool.
Split a vanilla bean lengthwise with a sharp knife and scrape out black suds, adding them to the butter.
Beat butter until fluffy adding salt, then the cheese and sour cream, blending thoroughly.
While mixing slowly add the cooled sauce.
Line a 2 to 2 1/2 quart paskha mold or clay flowerpot (with drain base) with cheesecloth.
Spoon cheese into cloth; fold cloth over top of cheese.
Place mold in a larger pan, elevating it so it can drain. Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Remove from mold.
Cover and keep cold until ready to serve.
Freeze to store.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spread 2/3 evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes and cool.
Beat egg whites and lemon juice with electric mixer until stiff.
Fold in strawberries and Cool Whip.
Pour over crust.
Top with remaining 1/3 crumb mixture.
Freeze.
Serve in squares.
Keeps well in airtight container in freezer up to 1 month.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and chocolate together.
Add milk.
Cook for about 10 minutes.
Add vanilla, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour in buttered dish.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and eggs together.
Add pumpkin and water; mix well.
In another bowl, add all dry ingredients; stir and mix well.
Add to 1st mixture.
Add dates, nuts and raisins and mix real well.
Put into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: layer salad
directions: In a large bowl break up lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Put layer of pepper, celery and onion on top of lettuce.
Spread uncooked peas on top of these vegetables.
Carefully spread salad dressing on top.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon bits on top. Seal with Saran and let set overnight.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Fix rice per package instructions.
Fix broccoli per package instructions.
Mix together in casserole dish.
In separate dish, add soup, Cheez Whiz and butter; microwave until melted.
Pour over rice and broccoli.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cake gets very brown.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass). Microwave chocolate and margarine in large bowl on High for 2 minutes or until melted. Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended. Mix in eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Do not overbake. Cool in pan. Cut into squares.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine sugar, flour and pineapple juice. Add cheese and tidbits.
Mix well.
Spoon into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine melted butter and Ritz cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: favorite icing
directions: Combine the milk and flour
in a saucepan.
Cook until thick. Cover and refrigerate.
In a medium mixing bowl, beat oleo, shortening, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add chilled milk/flour mixture and beat for 10 minutes.
Frost cooled cake.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream and butter together. Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into greased large casserole dish. Cover with grated cheese, bacon, chives and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Heat corn and cream cheese on stove.
When cream cheese is melted
add all other ingredients.	Put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over double boiler.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until velvety.

title: "the dream"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish or spray with Pam or whatever.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange broccoli in baking dish (I nuke my broccoli just to thaw it out).
Place cooked chicken on top of broccoli. Combine soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Pour this mixture over the chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with the shredded cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with butter or margarine and garlic powder.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbling and crumbs are brown.
Enjoy!!!!

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Sprinkle breasts with salt and pepper.
Heat corn oil in frypan over medium heat.
Place chicken in pan, skin side down; saute until golden brown.
In a bowl, mix together orange juice, soy sauce and flour until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, onion salt, Accent, mustard, vinegar and garlic powder.
Place browned chicken in large, shallow baking dish; pour sauce over chicken.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Add orange segments and green pepper; continue baking 5 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Serve sauce over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: australian pavlova
directions: Place egg whites and salt in bowl of electric mixer.
Beat on medium speed until egg whites are white, opaque and just beginning to hold their shape.
Add vinegar.
Increase speed to medium high and slowly add sugar, 1 tbsp. at a time, until all sugar is added and meringue is stiff. Beat in cornstarch.
Line baking sheet with parchment paper and draw 10 inch circle on paper.
Invert paper. Spread meringue in circle on prepared pan and using back of spoon, make meringue disk concave in center spreading from center to sides.
Bake meringue shell at 350° for 5 minutes.
Lower heat to 250° and continue baking 1 hour or until meringue is firm, crisp on outside and still slightly moist within.
Cool on pan on rack. When completely cooled, slide spatula or knife between meringue shell and paper to loosen.
If prepared in advance, wrap meringue with plastic wrap and store at room temperature.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and stir well.
Add sauteed mixture.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Top with a cracker crust, if desired.

title: holiday peppermint bark
directions: Line baking sheet with waxed paper. Microwave morsels in medium, microwave-safe bowl on Medium-High for 1 minute; stir. Microwave at additional 10 to 20 second intervals, stirring until smooth. Place peppermint candies in heavy-duty plastic bag. Crush candies using rolling pin. While holding strainer over melted morsels, pour crushed candy into strainer. Shake to release all small candy pieces; reserve larger candy pieces. Stir morsel-peppermint mixture. Spread mixture to desired thickness on prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle with reserved candy pieces; press in lightly. Let stand for about 1 hour or until firm. Break into pieces. Store in airtight container at room temperature.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream together	butter (or other shortening) and sugar. Add egg.
Measure and sift flour and spices.
Combine molasses and hot water.
To	first
mixture, add dry ingredients alternately with liquid.
Beat
after
each addition until smooth. Bake in paper lined cupcake pan in a 350° oven until done.

title: five hour stew
directions: Mix good and cover tight.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours; don't peek.
Sometimes I put 1 small can of peas and 1 can of green beans.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple; add Cool Whip, marshmallows, nuts and coconut.
Blend together and chill before serving.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all together and put paprika on top.

title: seven layer pea salad
directions: Place in long Pyrex dish in this order.
Place in refrigerator.
Garnish with bacon bits.

title: squash enchiladas with sour cream sauce and chili con queso
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and garlic and saute over medium heat until onion is translucent; do not allow to brown.
Stir in tomatoes, zucchini, yellow squash, cilantro, marjoram, thyme, oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Reduce heat to low and simmer vegetables 10 to 15 minutes or until the vegetables are crisp-tender.
Place corn tortillas in plastic wrap and microwave 2 minutes or until heated through.
One by one, roll the tortillas around some of the squash mixture and place, seam side down, in an ovenproof casserole that has been lightly coated with a nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Pour the Sour Cream Sauce over the rolled tortillas, then the Chili Con Queso.
Sprinkle lightly with grated cheese and heat in a 250° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or just until enchiladas are warmed through and cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: surprise
directions: You will need cupcake papers.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Use equal amounts of ingredients.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix.
Press all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add egg and raw rhubarb.
Coat well. Put mixture in pastry lined 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with crust. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes or until done.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Combine ground
beef,
rice and 1/2 of sauerkraut. Roll mixture in cabbage
leaves
that
have
been
dropped into boiling water for 1
minute
and drained.
Cover with tomatoes, tomato paste and remainder
of sauerkraut.
Cook on medium heat until cabbage is done.

title: sugar-free tarts
directions: Prepare pudding per directions on box; chill. Brown tart crusts as directed. Fill cooled tart crusts with chilled pudding. Refrigerate until ready to eat.
May use vanilla or chocolate pudding.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Boil water, sugar and gelatine 5 minutes.
Put cranberries in mixture; bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.

title: cheesy mushrooms(makes 3 dozen appetizers)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Finely chop stems.
Cook and stir mushroom stems, onions and garlic in 1/4 cup margarine over medium heat, about 5 minutes, until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except 1 tablespoon margarine.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet.
Break up with spoon or fork as it cooks.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until soft.
Add tomatoes, salt, cloves, chili powder and paprika.
Cover; simmer 2 hours.
Add hot water to keep from thickening (if necessary).
Add beans; heat thoroughly for 10 minutes.
Cover; refrigerate.
Heat before serving.

title: pap's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly.
Pat into loaf pan.
Spread some butter or oleo over top, then a strip of ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Sprinkle lemon juice on apples and place in buttered casserole.
Mix cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and sugar; sprinkle mixture over apples.
Combine flour, butter and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add crushed corn flakes and mix well.
Sprinkle this mixture over the apples.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pie crust
directions: To 2/3 cup sifted flour (Robin Hood or Gold Medal), add a dash of salt.
Add salad oil with water in the oil.
Add to dry ingredients all at once.
Mix with a fork.
Shape into 2 balls of dough with your hands.
Roll between 2 pieces of waxed paper. Makes 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix together oil and sugar.
Add half the sifted dry ingredients and mix well. Beat in carrots, pineapple, vanilla and nuts.
Add remaining sifted dry ingredients and beat until well blended.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add milk, flour, butter, blackberry jam, cinnamon, all spice, and cloves.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in 6 or 7 thin layers at 350°.
Let cool.
Add frosting.
Mix 1 box of Confectioner's sugar and milk until smooth. Then spread over each layer of the cake.

title: lentil soup
directions: Begin this soup in the morning, it should simmer all day. Simmer lentils, water and salt in a covered soup pot for 3 to 4 hours.
If you want to include meat, add it at the same time. Steam or saute in butter the garlic, onion, celery and carrots. Add to the lentils after they've simmered 3 to 4 hours.
Continue to simmer (low heat!).
Add to the soup about 30 minutes before serving: black pepper, tomatoes, red wine, lemon juice, molasses or brown sugar and wine vinegar.
Sprinkle extra vinegar and freshly chopped scallions onto each serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
(I make 4 times this amount for the Oasis.)

title: corn souffle
directions: My pioneer aunt gave this recipe to a young lady in the early days.
This lady told me the
recipe as she remembered it.

title: hearty potato sauerkraut soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over low heat.

title: lo-cal ranch dip
directions: Mix well with fork or wire whisk.
Store in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: red pepper shrimp calabrese
directions: In a nonreactive large fry pan, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add garlic and hot pepper flakes and cook about 30 seconds, or until fragrant.
Stir shrimp into pan and cook 1 to 2 minutes to coat with oil.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut cheese into thin strips and toss with flour.
In large bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add half and half, onion, bacon, pepper and cheese; mix well.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted just off center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, sugar and butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Mix jello, water and frozen raspberries and place in mold.
Chill until set.
Beat softened cheese and sugar.
Add whipped topping and beat.
Spread over chilled jello.
Place pretzel mixture on top.
Chill.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in angel food pan.
Mix first 5 ingredients and pour over melted butter, but do not mix with butter.
Heat fruit to boiling and pour on top of batter.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°. This can be doubled for a large family.

title: ruby red cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add all ingredients except nuts.
When Jell-O begins to congeal, add nuts.
Chill overnight. Serves 12 as an accompaniment or as a salad.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press into 9 x 10-inch pan until firm.
Melt 2 sticks oleo, add powdered sugar and mix well.
Add egg whites and beat 15 minutes or more on high speed.
Spread over crust.
Slice bananas on top, then cover with pineapple (drained).
Spread with Cool Whip.
Top with cherries and nuts.
Chill.

title: frittata with broccoli and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In oven type broilerproof skillet, cook potatoes in canola oil over medium heat, stirring occasionally for about 10 minutes until tender and slightly browned.
Add broccoli, mushrooms and onion and cook another 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Drain broccoli in colander or wire strainer for an hour before mixing in the bread.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes (defrosted), 1/2 cup butter, salt and pepper. Add sour cream, cheese and soup.
Blend thoroughly and pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining butter with corn flakes and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and cook until veggies are tender. Make a paste of milk and flour; add to veggies and cook until smooth and thick, stirring often. Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted; do not add salt.

title: frosty date balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Stir in water and vanilla. Add flour and dash of salt.
Mix well.
Stir in dates and nuts. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 300° about 20 minutes or until cookies are set but not brown.
While warm, roll with powdered sugar.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine all ingredients except the nuts.
Bring to a soft boil. Add nuts and stir until all are well covered.
Pour out on marble slab or buttered platter. Separate the nuts.

title: chocolate kiss thumbprint
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, sugar, milk, vanilla and egg yolk.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add melted chocolate; mix well.
Combine flour and salt. Add to chocolate mixture.
Mix until blended.
Form dough into 1 inch balls.
Beat egg white slightly with fork.
Coat balls with egg white.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Press thumb gently in center of each cookie. Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place chocolate Kiss in each thumbprint.
Return to oven for 1 minute.
Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen 2 inch cookies.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, onion soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Crunch cereal and stir in remaining margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: zucchini crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well and fry in olive oil.

title: pineapple pimento salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: budweiser bird
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Mix flour, salt and pepper together and lightly flour chicken.
Saute chicken in margarine. Remove to platter and saute onion in same pan.
Sprinkle onion with parsley, thyme and salt, then return chicken to pan, turning until chicken is well coated with onion mixture.
Pour beer over chicken and stir in mushrooms.
Poke chicken with fork so it will pick up flavor.
Place in casserole dish and bake, covered in a 325° oven 1 hour.
Serve sauce with chicken.
Serves 6.

title: antioch salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Just before serving, add remaining ingredients.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook
onion and pepper in butter; add remaining ingredients to chicken broth.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: 7 layer salad(lo-cal)
directions: Layer the first 7 ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Mix yogurt and sweetener and spoon over salad.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.
Place Corn Dodgers in mixing pan.
Add cream of celery soup, cream of chicken soup and the chicken broth.
Mix well.
Add eggs, chopped celery, onion and black pepper, if desired.
Mix all ingredients well.
Add additional chicken broth if needed.
Pour 1/2 of mix in baking pan. Place cooked chicken over mix.
Then add remaining mix on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage in medium skillet until browned; drain and set aside.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles; place triangles with elongated points toward center in a greased large pizza pan. Press bottom and side to form a crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on lower oven rack.
Crust will be puffy when removed from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Spoon sausage over dough; sprinkle with cheeses.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients; pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° on lower oven rack for 30 to 35 minutes. Garnish with green and red pepper slices, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: seafood pizza
directions: Combine cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce to taste and garlic to taste.
Spread into a Pyrex pie pan or quiche dish.
Combine ketchup and 1 teaspoon horseradish (or horseradish to taste). Spread over cream cheese.
Cut shrimp and imitation crab into small pieces.
Spread over ketchup mixture.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: beefy bean soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine cabbage, water and onion; bring to boiling.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in undrained lima beans and undiluted soup.
Cut corned beef into small cubes.
Carefully stir into soup.
Heat through.
Yield:
6 to 7 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all the spices together, then add pumpkin, eggs and Eagle Brand milk, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 420° for 15 minutes, then turn down to 350° and bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: fat free pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse with cold water.
Put in a large bowl and pour in salad dressing and all vegetables.
Stir and season with garlic salt to taste.
You can add white vinegar if you like it very tart.
Chill.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Prepare pumpkin by following the directions on the can. Pour mixture into a lightly greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle 3/4 of the dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture. Slice butter over top of cake mix and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 30 minutes.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Boil grits and water for 5 minutes.
Add butter.
Spray casserole with Pam and pour grits mixture in.
Add 1 cup shredded sharp Cheddar cheese, salt and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together thoroughly.
Place in greased ring mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold onto serving plate and place strawberry jam in the center of ring.
Serve with crackers. Must be prepared one day in advance.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Defrost berries.
Dissolve Jell-O.
Mix all ingredients except sour cream.
Chill 1/2 mixture in pan.
When firm, spread sour cream on top and then pour rest of Jell-O mixture on top and chill.

title: spinach sandwich spread
directions: Mix all and chill.
Good dip or spread.

title: pop-over pizza
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Stir in sauce mix, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Beat eggs, oil and milk until foamy. Beat in flour and salt until smooth.
Pour batter over meat filling; spread to cover completely.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge loaf cake
directions: Put the flour and sugar into a mixing bowl; mix well.
Put the cocoa, water, margarine and vanilla in a saucepan.
Let this come to a boil; pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well, then add the eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn and black bean salad
directions: Toss together corn, black beans, pepper, salsa and scallions. Serve hot or cold.

title: zucchini rounds with ham spread
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients, except zucchini; mix well.
Spread or pipe about 1 teaspoon of mixture onto each zucchini slice.
If desired, garnish with carrot curls, fresh chives or parsley.
Makes 24 to 28 appetizers.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt until it feels like cornmeal. Stir water, egg and vinegar together; add liquids to dry for right consistency.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat the whole egg and yolks together until light and fluffy. Add salt and water.
Work in flour.
Roll out on floured board with rolling pin until thin.
Cut into squares and roll into logs. Cut logs in thin slices and separate noodles and lie out to dry. Then dry noodles can be frozen or used in favorite recipes.

title: apricot loaf
directions: Mix
together
flour,
baking
powder,	soda,
salt and sugar. In
a
separate bowl, mix together eggs, butter, milk, apricots and
nuts.	Add flour mixture to apricot mixture and stir
only until
moistened.
Pour
into a greased bread pan. Let stand
20 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven about 60 minutes or until it tests done.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add cream cheese, a little at a time, until mixed together. Clean mushrooms and fill with sausage mixture and place on jelly roll pan.
Place small pat of butter on each one.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20-30 minutes, or until heated through.

title: chile cheese ball(serves 2 one pound balls)
directions: In food processor or large mixing bowl, thoroughly blend cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add chiles, onion and Worcestershire; blend carefully so chiles are not mashed.
Chill several hours.
Divide in half and shape into 2 balls.
Roll each ball in nuts.
Chill overnight.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: mary jane's bean dip
directions: Brown ground round and onion.
Add beans and taco sauce; put in casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese, then Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger potpourri
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion and garlic in large saucepan or Dutch oven until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice and chop onions.
Saute in butter until limp.
Sprinkle with flour, pepper, garlic powder, sugar, parsley and thyme.
Cook until golden brown.
Add enough water to consomme to make 1 quart. Combine with onion mixture and add wine; simmer 45 minutes.
At the last minute, stir in cognac (no more than 2 tablespoons).

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir water, 1/4 cup of the salsa, margarine and contents of vegetable/seasoning packet in 2-quart baking pan.
Stir in stuffing crumbs to moisten.
Arrange chicken over stuffing.
Pour remaining salsa over chicken.
Loosely cover pan with foil; bake for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; remove to serving plate.
Fluff stuffing with fork; serve with chicken.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for 35 or 45 minutes or until done.

title: bit o' the irish pudding dessert
directions: Combine pudding mix with milk and beat with mixer on medium speed for two minutes.
Spread pudding over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix ingredients.
If dough is not consistent to touch, add more applesauce.
Knead for few minutes; roll to desired thickness.
Cut with metal cookie cutter.
Using a straw, poke a hole for hanging.
Let dry 2 to 3 days on aluminum pan.
Transfer to cooling rack to dry the back.
Spray with craft glaze and store in Ziploc bag.
Use a ribbon for hanging.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in hot water; add cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add strawberries (frozen), cut up.
Let congeal.
Fold in Cool Whip and ice cream.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl and mix well. Pour into greased casserole. Combine 2 1/2 tablespoons butter, brown sugar, pecans and flour in bowl and mix until crumbly. Sprinkle over sweet potato mixture. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbly.

title: creamy corn
directions: In a medium skillet over low heat, stir cream cheese with milk, margarine and onion salt until smooth.
Add corn (do not drain corn) and heat, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.

title: dill okra
directions: Pack scrubbed okra into hot, sterilized pint jars with a few celery leaves, clove of garlic and 1 head and stem dill for each jar.
Make brine of water, vinegar and salt.
Heat to boiling. Pour over jarred okra.
Seal and process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 6 pints.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Cook sausage; then add cheese.
Beat milk and eggs.
Add to sausage mix; then pour into pie shell.
Cook 45 minutes or until firm at 350°.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine first 7 ingredients in a mixing bowl and blend well. Pour into a greased and floured 9 1/2 inch bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake springs bake when touched.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in tight container.
For long-term storage, the freezer keeps the powdered milk fresh.
Use 3 to 4 tablespoons in a cup of hot water.

title: apple mull(hot drink)
directions: Put cranberry and apple juice into a 30-cup percolator.
Place other ingredients in basket.
Perk.
Take out basket.
Serves 40 cups.

title: pizza casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, pepper, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add macaroni and sauce and heat mixture thoroughly.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cooked squash and grated cheese.
Add all other ingredients, then top with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Break cake into pieces size of walnuts.
Melt chocolate chips and cool slightly.
Dissolve gelatine in water, add to melted chips.
In separate bowl, beat eggs until foamy, then mix in with chocolate.
Butter the bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then add a layer of cake pieces.
Pour half the chocolate mixture over the cake, then add another layer of cake and the rest of the chocolate.
Spread cake with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Chill for 24 hours.
Cover with foil.

title: french fried mushrooms
directions: Organize ingredients as follows:
Put the 1/4 cup milk in a small bowl.
Put flour on sheet of waxed paper.
Beat egg with the 2 tablespoons milk in another small bowl.
Mix bread crumbs and oregano on sheet of waxed paper.
Have ready 1 or 2 small racks.

title: chocolate amaretto mousse pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with aluminum foil; press the foil firmly against the surface of the plate, making the foil as smooth as possible.
Melt 1 cup of the chocolate pieces with 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Pour into foil-lined plate and quickly smooth over the bottom and up the side.
Place in freezer until it is firm, about 30 minutes.

title: corn quiche
directions: Take 1 egg white and brush over pie shell.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion in butter until golden.
Sprinkle pie shell with cheese, then ham, then onion.
Beat egg slightly and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well combined.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden.

title: ginger ale pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar; continue to cream until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flavoring, then add flour and ginger ale alternately.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Freezes very well.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender on liquify.
Store in refrigerator.

title: meat loaf with sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients (except for tomato paste) thoroughly. Form
into
two
loaves.
Bake
for 30 minutes in oven at 350°. Spread
tomato
paste over top of loaves.
Bake 45 more minutes. Total baking time is 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Pour chopped pecans in the bottom.
Place rolls on top of the nuts.
Pour butterscotch pudding (the cooked kind) over rolls.
Melt butter or margarine with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour this mixture over the pudding.
Cover with wax paper and let sit out overnight.
Bake the next day at 350° for 35 minutes.
I cover the top of the pan lightly with foil after about 20 minutes so that the top doesn't get so brown.
Turn upside-down as soon as taken out of oven.

title: beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown stew beef in small amount of oil.
Add carrots and onions.
When they are almost brown, pour enough water to cover meat and vegetables.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Mix about 1/4 to 1/2 cup flour in a cup of water.
Pour this into beef to make gravy.

title: nuttose
directions: Mix ingredients with water until consistency of whipping cream.
Steam 2 1/2 hours.

title: salmon ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain liquid from salmon.
Combine ingredients.
Form into ball and chill.
Serves well with most crackers.

title: chuck's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put chicken into casserole dish.
Add pepper, carrots and potatoes.
Pour dressing on top.
Bake 40 minutes.
Take up chicken (leave vegetables in dish with top on it).
Put chicken on grill after putting on blackening for 5 to 10 minutes, until brown.
Serve with vegetables.

title: cashew clusters
directions: Combine butterscotch morsels and chocolate morsels in a saucepan;
cook
over
low	heat,
stirring
until morsels are melted.
Remove from heat and add cashew pieces; stir to coat. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool completely.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat.
Drain grease and add taco seasoning and water according to seasoning package.
Let cool.
Add chopped tomatoes, peppers and cheese.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, add crushed Doritos and Catalina dressing and mix it all together.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Cream shortening, peanut
butter, brown sugar and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add
vanilla
and eggs and beat until smooth. Then add remaining ingredients.
Spread in prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: whole wheat honey bread
directions: Combine yeast, flour and whole wheat flour in bowl.
Combine milk, honey, shortening and salt.
Heat to lukewarm and stir to dissolve.
Add to dry ingredients and mix on low 1/2 minute and high for 3 minutes.
Stir in an additional 2 1/2 cups flour and knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and let dough rest 15 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves or rolls.
Let rise.
Bake loaves at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or rolls for 20 minutes.

title: orange chicken
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in flour; brown.
Place in casserole. Cover with green onions and drizzle with juice.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°; uncover and continue to bake for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: old-fashioned pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1/3 cup butter in 10-inch cast iron skillet.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar; stir until blended.
Drain pineapple well; reserve 2 tablespoons syrup.
Arrange pineapple in butter-sugar mixture.
Place cherry in center.
Beat remaining 1/3 cup butter with 1/2 cup granulated sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, lemon peel and juice and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with sour cream and 2 tablespoons pineapple syrup.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks. Gradually beat in remaining 1/4 cup granulated sugar to make stiff meringue.
Fold into batter.
Pour over pineapple in skillet.
Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes until cake tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes, then invert onto serving plate. Serves 8.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash and dry tender young okra.
Pack in clean jars.
Add 1 clove garlic and 1 pod red pepper to each pint jar.
Mix vinegar, water and salt. Bring to a boil and pour over okra and seal.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add the flavorings. Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt to the flour and sift.
Mix in carefully the butter, eggs and sugar mixture.
Add the sour cream, reserving 2 tablespoons of the sour cream and mix with the baking soda; blend into the batter and mix thoroughly.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan; pour in batter and bake at 325° for 75 minutes, longer if your oven is slow.

title: apple-carrot casserole
directions: Combine sugar, rind, flour and salt.
Place 1/2 of the apples in buttered dish, then 1/2 of the carrots.
Cover with 1/2 of the sugar mixture.
Repeat.
Pour orange juice over all and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: red rice
directions: Fry bacon, remove and place on paper towel.
Brown onion and bell pepper in drippings.
Add tomatoes, sauce, Tabasco and bacon. Pour in greased casserole; sprinkle top with cheese and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Place sliced apples in unbaked pastry shell.
Combine 1/2 cup of the sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar with flour; cut in butter or margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until apples are tender; cool.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Add 1 medium size bottle Italian dressing and mayonnaise for creamy look.
This is a large recipe. I just make about half of it.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or 4 small pans.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer at high speed, beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
Add oil; beat well.
At low speed, add dry ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Turn into pans.
Bake about 35 minutes for small loaves.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes for large loaves.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar and shortening by hand.
Pour warm milk overnight and stir.
Add beaten egg and dissolved yeast.
Add flour and salt. Let rise to double in size, covered for approximately 2 hours. Knead for about 5 minutes.
Roll and cut in desired shapes.
Let rise again, then bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican appetizers
directions: Mix cheese, jalapenos and olives.
Spread mixture over each tortilla.
Roll up and chill for at least one hour.
When ready to serve, slice each tortilla into 8 portions and secure with toothpicks.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Cool.
Put in punch bowl and add ice cream.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Cover bottom with single layer of crackers.
Sprinkle pecans over crackers. Melt butter and sugar; boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Prepare either a pastry or a crumb crust shell in an 8-inch pie pan.
Combine sugar, egg yolks and melted butter.
Add raisins, cream, vinegar, salt and spices.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
You may add 1 teaspoon vanilla here.
Turn into the pan.
If using a pastry crust, bake for 10 minutes at 425°, then 20 minutes more at 350°.
Cool before serving.

title: guava chicken
directions: Cut chicken thighs in half.
Cut slits in meat.
Marinate in sauce overnight, turning occasionally.
Cook over charcoal or in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan with one package of crescent rolls.
Spread hamburger and oregano on the crust. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Top with pizza sauce.
Place second package of crescent rolls over this.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, until rolls on top are done and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend sugar, brown sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix together and drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°. Watch carefully and remove when lightly browned.

title: corned beef casserole *
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add onion, pepper and butter.
Cook until a little brown.
Add corned beef and tomato paste, water and seasoning.
Cook until thick, but not dry.
Drain macaroni and add to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Top with grated cheese.
Serve hot.

title: tuna gumbo salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 c. boiling water.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill to set.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in oven in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and then remove from oven.
In large bowl beat eggs, add flour, milk, salt and baking powder and mix well.
Add cheese and thawed spinach and pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes if using glass Pyrex.
If using a metal cake pan, bake for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven, cool for 45 minutes and cut into squares.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Cream oleo and brown sugar, then add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda and salt. Mix well and add oats. Set aside. In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips, condensed milk, oleo and salt. Add nuts and vanilla. Spread 2/3 dough in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with chocolate mixture. Swirl rest of dough on top of chocolate filling. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool. Cut and place on rack. Freezes well.

title: strawberry-coconut nests
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Remove small amount of center from each dessert cup; frost cups with cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut. Spoon strawberries into centers at serving time.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: english suet pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients adding salt to taste.
Pour into greased mold.
Steam 2 hours.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat together oil and sugar.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add apples, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Bake in two 1-pound loaf pans at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: perfect hostess stew
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a Dutch oven or roasting pan. Cover tightly and place in an oven at 350° for 4 hours. About 1/2 hour before serving, uncover and cook remaining time uncovered. Serves 10.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put 3 1/2 liters of popped corn in a large paper bag (no unpopped kernels).

title: dime-a-dip rice
directions: Brown sausage.
Add onions, pepper and celery.
Bring water to boil.
Add rice and soup.
Bring to boil.
Add sausage mixture. Add all remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Baked uncovered the first 40 minutes, then uncover and bake the remaining time.

title: pepperidge farm chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan with a piece of Swiss cheese over each piece of chicken.
Drizzle soup over top, then buttered crumbs.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Saute pressed garlic in corn oil (on medium heat, do not brown garlic).
Add 1 stick margarine and broccoli to this mixture.
Sprinkle with bouillon and black pepper.
Simmer broccoli while pasta is cooking.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Place all dry ingredients except 1 cup of the flour.
Using dough hook, turn mixer on low to mix dry ingredients.
Heat milk, water and shortening until shortening melts.
Cool (to 105° to 115°).
Gradually add liquid to dry mixture (low speed).
Mix about 2 minutes.
Continuing at low speed gently tap remaining flour.
Mix until dough clings to hook and cleans sides of bowl. Place dough in a greased bowl and cover.
Store dough in refrigerator at least 2 hours or until needed.
Shape dough on a floured board into clover leaf or your favorite dinner roll.
Let rise in a warm place until light, about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: braunschweiger chip dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream in a bowl; mix with electric mixer.
When smooth and well mixed, stir in sour cream. Chill for 2 hours.
Serve with chips or snack crackers.
Yields 23 to 35 servings.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix all together.
Put 1 heaping tablespoon mixture in center of corn tortilla (that has been dipped in hot oil) and roll. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put remaining mixture on top and spread to cover enchiladas.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Makes 18.

title: crock-pot sweet and sour pork
directions: Place ingredients in a crock-pot and cook until done!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Bring to a boil in a large kettle the beef, bouillon, water, onions, celery, carrots, barley, bay leaf, salt and pepper. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 hours or until meat is very tender. Discard bay leaf. Add cabbage, potatoes and succotash. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in tomatoes. Heat.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts or 12 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain.
Spread crescent rolls onto 12-inch pizza pan.
Seal perforations and press up sides of pan. Spread sausage over crescent crust.
Sprinkle on potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: broccoli and cauliflower with nut-cracker crumb topping
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, cut broccoli flowerets and stems into 2 1/2 x 1-inch pieces.
Cut cauliflower into 2 1/2 x 1-inch pieces.
In a 12-inch skillet over high heat, in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook broccoli, stirring quickly and constantly, until evenly coated with oil.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 cup water.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 2 minutes.
Uncover and stir-fry broccoli 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Remove broccoli to bowl.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Do not pare cucumbers; slice them thinly.
Add onions, peppers, whole garlic cloves and salt.
Cover with cracked ice and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumber mixture; heat just to boil.
Seal in hot, sterilized canning jars.
Yields 8 pints.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Thaw potatoes.
Combine them with rest of ingredients.
Use a 3-quart casserole or long flat dish.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Put one vanilla wafer in the bottom of a cupcake paper.
Whip together all other ingredients until smooth.
Fill paper 1/2 full. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Top with fruit and chill. Makes about 20.

title: ronnie's hot chili
directions: Cook hamburger meat, drain grease.
Add beans, tomatoes and other ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: wine cake
directions: In large mixing bowl combine cake mix and pudding mix.
Add eggs, oil, juice, wine and vodka.
Beat on low speed of an electric mixer for half a minute.
Beat on medium speed for 5 minutes, scrape bowl frequently.
Pour into greased and

title: german red cabbage
directions: Coat the inside of a large Dutch oven with nonstick cooking spray.
Saute onion and apple until tender.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until tender (about 1 hour).
Serve hot or cold.

title: summer sparkle punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; stir in lemonade.
Add ginger ale and ice cubes.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: citrus cream punch
directions: In a large pitcher, combine juices and water.
In punch bowl, place the sherbet and ice cream.
Pour juice mixture over the sherbet and ice cream and circulate it until pourable.
Yield: about 40 punch cup servings.

title: peach fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine peach pie filling, pineapple chunks, oranges, grapes, bananas and marshmallows.
If making ahead of time, omit bananas and marshmallows until ready to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lime cucumber pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with lime and 2 gallons water. Soak 24 hours. Rinse; cover with clear water. Soak for 3 hours, changing water each hour. Heat vinegar and dissolve sugar. Add pickling spice and cinnamon. Add cucumbers when cool and let set overnight. Cook for 35 minutes on simmer. Pack in jars and seal.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems.
Set caps and stems aside.
Preheat oven to 450°.
In 10-inch skillet, cook chopped sausage until well browned.
With slotted spoon, remove sausage and drain on paper towel.
Spoon off all but 2 tablespoons drippings. In hot drippings, cook mushroom stems until tender.
Remove from heat, stir in sausage, cheese and bread crumbs.
Fill mushroom caps with sausage mixture and place in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Shred and fry slowly until done.
Best to do the day before you combine the rolls.
Cook all the liquid out.
Put in refrigerator; the colder this is, the better the seal on the rolls.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; press into large baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Mix together next 3 ingredients (save approximately 1/2 of whipped topping for top).
Spread over cooled crust.
Bring to a boil the berries, sugar, water and cornstarch; cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice.
Cool.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining whipped topping when ready to serve.

title: chicken 'n' dumplins
directions: In a large pot, cook whole
chicken for approximately 2 hours or
until
tender
(chicken will pull from bones).
When chicken is done, remove from broth and tear from bones, saving for later use.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour and cut in shortening until light coarse crumbs.
Blend in just enough milk so
that dough
forms
a
ball and leaves sides of bowl. Knead dough gently
on a lightly floured surface.
Roll dough with rolling pin until thin.
Cut into thin strips.
Drop into boiling broth of chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes over medium heat.
Add chicken pieces; simmer 8 to 10 minutes. Add yellow food coloring, if desired.

title: instant salad
directions: Mix together the fruits and juice with pudding.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
(The pudding mix thickens the fruit juice to make a delicious dressing.)

title: fresh tomato cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in tomatoes, nuts, dates and raisins.
Put into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Sift together the flour and salt.
Mix, to a batter, with unbeaten eggs and milk, beating until the mixture is smooth and creamy.
If made an hour or more before baking, the pudding will be lighter than if prepared at the last moment.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and sugar together in casserole. Add margarine, oats, brown sugar and nuts; mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: best easy beef stew
directions: Layer beef cubes and mushrooms in a large baking dish. Sprinkle soup mix over mushrooms.
Spoon mushroom soup on top. Arrange carrots and potatoes around edge of baking dish.
Bake tightly covered at 300° for 3 hours.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: crunchy vegetable medley
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter in a large skillet until onion is tender.
Add water and bouillon granules, stirring until granules are dissolved.
Add next 6 ingredients; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low and cook 5 minutes.
Drain well. Combine vegetables and next 6 ingredients, tossing gently.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: coconut jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in layers at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Ice with caramel icing.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Add butter, milk, salt, cheese and pepper.
Cook on low until all the cheese is melted; stir often.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: thanksgiving apple-cherry pie
directions: Mix flour and salt well.
Cut in shortening and butter until coarse crumbs.
Add water and vinegar, mixing with fork.
Form in ball.
Roll out.
Carefully lift to pie plate (pastry is tender and may tear).
Makes pastry for 2-crust 8 or 9-inch pie or 2 shells.

title: company squash casserole
directions: Place squash and onion in boiling salted water, just enough to cover.
Cover and cook 5 minutes; drain well and set aside.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a heavy saucepan over hot heat; add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Combine the squash mixture, cheese sauce and mushrooms; spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a small saucepan; stir in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Sprinkle mixture over squash.
Bake casserole at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all three cans of soup together with the rice and pour into pan.
Dip chicken parts in melted margarine and lay on top of rice.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours.

title: poppy seed cake
