directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use Bundt pan (greased and floured). Garnish with poppy seed sprinkles or glaze.

title: hot chicken salad(great for luncheons)
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new potatoes
directions: Peel or scrub tiny new potatoes.
Cook in boiling salted water 15 or 20 minutes, drain.
Make a white sauce of the remaining ingredients.
Combine potatoes and sauce.

title: carrot cake
directions: Add sugar to eggs.
Beat well.
Add Wesson oil; mix well. Sift dry ingredients 3 times and mix with carrots and nuts.
Add to the egg mixture and mix well.
Pour into 3 well-greased layer cake pans and bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: decorating frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat 10 minutes on high.

title: cornmeal pancakes
directions: Combine cornmeal, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Add water slowly.
Cover; let stand 10 minutes.
Mix flour and baking powder; set aside.
In a small bowl, beat egg, milk and butter until smooth.
Pour into cornmeal, then add flour mixture.
Stir only until combined.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Roll spareribs in flour and brown in fat.
Put in baking pan. Melt butter and brown onion.
Add rest of ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over ribs.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chile beans
directions: Cook ground beef; drain fat.
Add onion, pinto beans, kidney beans, diced tomatoes, chili mix and salt to taste.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes on medium.

title: kringel(estonian birthday cake)
directions: Place saffron in cup of boiling water for 20 minutes and pour through a fine sieve into a large bowl.
Add yeast, whipping cream and 1 1/4 cups flour.
Mix well. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of flour over the mixture and let rise.

title: fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan on stove.
Add remaining ingredients slowly.
Cook until thick.
Pour into buttered pan.
Refrigerate until cool before slicing.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cold water, cornstarch and food coloring and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add jello and strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell and place in refrigerator until set.
Top with whipped topping when ready to serve.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Melt margarine in pie pan; mix in flour, 4 tablespoons sugar and half of nuts.
Spread with fingers to fit pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown; cool crust.

title: apple dessert cake(so easy to make and so delicious to eat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add creamed mixture. Stir in diced apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold, with or without whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pea soup
directions: Rinse peas; remove off color or impurities.
Cover with cold water; soak at least 12 hours.
Drain the soaked peas; cover with fresh water and bring to a boil.
Lower heat; simmer for several hours.
Remove any scum or froth from the top.
Add ham hocks, chicken bouillon, minced onion and diced carrots.
Continue to cook until peas begin to soften to a mush.
Stir frequently.

title: pea salad
directions: Lay
in
layers
the leaf lettuce, chopped celery, bell pepper and
green
onion, then peas.
Mix together the mayonnaise and sugar;
put on top of peas, then top with bacon and grated cheese.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together the corn meal, soda and salt.
Mix together the milk, bacon drippings or oil, eggs and corn.
Combine both mixtures.
Mix together the peppers, onion and cheese.
Pour half the batter in greased pan and put the peppers, onion and cheese in the middle.
Pour the rest of the batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until done.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool.
Combine sugar and water.
Bring to quick boil to dissolve sugar.
Remove from fire and cool.
Combine dissolved jello and sugar water.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice; put into container and freeze.
Best made 2 days before using.
Remove from container into punch bowl; add ginger ale and break up frozen punch.
Take from freezer 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 2-quart casserole.

title: salmon log
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill several hours. Shape into a log and roll in parsley flakes and chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco; add sugar gradually.
Beat until creamy; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes in 300° oven.

title: treasure bars
directions: Beat
brown sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla; add
sifted
dry
ingredients (flour, baking powder and salt).
Stir in peanuts,
coconut and chocolate chips.
Pour over bottom mixture.
Bake 25 minutes more.

title: chicken cheese bake
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, place chicken.
Top with cheese.
Stir soup and spread over cheese.
Top with tomato slices.
Combine butter and stuffing; sprinkle over tomatoes. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Serve over rice.

title: apple fritters
directions: In mixing bowl, combine first five ingredients.
Lightly beat eggs with water; add to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Fold in apples.
In a skillet, heat oil to 375°.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into oil and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll in sugar.
Serve warm.
Yields 40 fritters.

title: french toast
directions: Cook butter, brown sugar and corn syrup until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix eggs, milk, vanilla and nutmeg. Set aside.
Layer cut up bread on top of syrup mixture in pan.
Pour egg mixture over bread slices. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Syrup is optional. Serves 6 to 8.

title: one rise monkey bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients with 1 1/2 cup flour and beat together for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour forming a ball and knead this for about 1 minute.
Roll the dough into a square approximately 15 x 12 inches and cut diagonal strips first from left to right then right to left forming diamond shapes approximately 2 inches long.
Lay pieces into the bottom of a greased tube or Bundt pan allowing overlapping.
After you have layered the first half of the dough, start dipping each piece into melted butter and continuing to layer until finished.
Allow dough to rise until doubled, then bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes and turn out on plate to serve.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Combine water and black-eyed peas in a large saucepan.
Cook until almost tender, about 1 hour (add more water if needed). Heat shortening or oil in medium skillet on medium heat.
Add green pepper, onion, garlic, cumin and thyme; cook and stir until browned.
Add tomato paste and chili powder.
Stir and add a little water, then stir and pour onto beans.
Add rice, bacon, salt and pepper.
Stir; cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in bowl until foamy.
Add sugar, vanilla and mixture of flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Stir in oil, dates, nuts and zucchini; mix well.
Divide between 2 lightly greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.
Cool on wire rack then remove from pans.

title: tomato florentine soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute onions in butter over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add chicken stock, tomatoes, parsley, bay leaves, paprika, sugar and salt and pepper to onions in pan.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: green goddess salad
directions: Mix jello; set until it quivers.
Add softened cream cheese or cottage cheese.
(Cream cheese can be softened in microwave oven.) Fold in crushed pineapple with the juice.
Add Cool Whip; let set until firm.

title: good day granola
directions: Stir oats, brown sugar, bran, wheat germ, nuts and sunflower seeds in a large bowl.
Put vegetable oil, honey and vanilla in a small saucepan.
Heat, stirring, until bubbly.
Pour liquid over dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: white brownies
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Place in 8 x 8-inch pan, greased well and lined with wax paper, lined again.
Grease side of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: victorian lemon pecan cake
directions: Using 8-inch round layer cake pans, mix, bake and cool cake as directed.
Spread frosting between layers and on sides of cake. Combine preserves and hot water; brush over top of cake.
Press nuts into frosting on sides of cake.

title: french bread dinner
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Split the French bread loaf lengthwise.
Spread Cheez Whiz on the bread faces.
Brown hamburger and put on bread.
Drizzle the tomato sauce over the meat.
Spread the onion and mushrooms on top.
Sprinkle down the center with oregano.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry lasagna
directions: Beat cream cheese, pudding mixes, sugar and milk in large bowl until smooth. In another bowl, mix strawberries, vanilla and sugar well. Reserve 1 cup strawberry mixture. Slice cake in 1/2-inch slices. Line bottom of 9 x 13 pan with cake. Put 1/3 of the cream cheese mixture carefully on top. Add 1/3 of the strawberry mixture on top. Repeat layers again two times. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until served. Top each serving with a teaspoon of pureed strawberries in reserve.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook spiral and round noodles; put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown sausage and drain.
Layer on noodles:
sausage, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cover with pepperoni.
Mix spaghetti sauce, seasoning and tomato sauce.
Pour over layers.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 250°.

title: macho nachos
directions: Layer chips, beans, cheese, jalapeno peppers and olives on large plate, at least 2 layers of everything.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix together butter, milk, sugar, salt and cocoa; boil ingredients for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix and spoon onto waxed paper; cool.

title: baked pumpkin pudding
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Crack the eggs into the large mixing bowl.

Beat them with a fork until they are light yellow. Add the canned pumpkin to the eggs and mix with wooden spoon. Measure the cinnamon, ginger and allspice into the mixing bowl. Add the molasses and milk, stir well.
Use paper towels to grease the casserole dish with butter or shortening.
Pour the pumpkin mixture into the casserole dish.
Bake the pudding for 1 hour, then take the casserole dish out of the oven.
Put the casserole dish on a trivet at the table and serve the pudding.

title: governor's mansion brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler.
Cool this mixture.
Beat eggs and salt until light in color and foamy in texture.
Add sugar and vanilla gradually and continue beating until well creamed.
Combine the cooled chocolate mixture and the egg/sugar mixture.
Fold in the sifted flour.
Add the pecans.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: green corn tamale pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain and save liquid from corn.
Mix corn, masa, chilies, butter, sugar, salt and cheese.
Add the corn liquid.
(If there isn't enough liquid to make 2/3 cup, add water for the remainder.)
Pour into buttered 8-inch square casserole. Set casserole into pan filled with boiling water and bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift 2 1/2 cups flour, spice, soda, and salt together.
Add pumpkin and sugar mixture.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Blend well after each additions.
Combine nuts and remaining flour.
Add vanilla last.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked peeled potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Roll each half in melted butter. Sprinkle paprika and salt over potatoes.
Roll potatoes in bread crumbs.
Lay flat in Pam-sprayed pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, salt and vanilla; add sugar and egg . Mix well; add flour and baking powder alternately with pineapple.
Add nuts and oats, mixing well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 18 minutes.
Very moist and chewy.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients, except stick cinnamon.
Place in an airtight container.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix cream cheese, marshmallow cream and almond flavoring together. Cut bananas into 1 1/2-inch pieces and dip into mix. Roll in coconut and place on tray. Serve.

title: kathryn's sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Set in a cool place.
When ready to bake, roll them out and cut in desired shapes with a cookie cutter. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven, until brown at edges.

title: irish beef stew
directions: Heat oil in large pot over medium-high heat.
Add beef and saute until well browned on all sides.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute.
Add beef broth, tomato paste, sugar, thyme, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaves and parsley.
Stir to combine. Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: creamy deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.	Remove yolk and put in deep bowl; place whites on plate or tray.
With electric mixer, break up yolks, adding 1 tablespoon mayonnaise at a time until smooth and creamy.
Add yellow mustard and salt to taste.	Fill egg white bowls with mixture and chill.

title: kiss pudding
directions: Scald 1 1/2 cups milk.
Mix yolks with fork and add sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup cold milk. Add scalded milk to cold mixture.
Return to the saucepan and cook over direct heat until it boils.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Pour into dessert dishes and chill.

title: chicken "n" dumplings
directions: In Dutch oven, bring chicken, water and salt to a boil. Turn down and simmer 1 hour or until tender. Remove from broth and cool. Bone chicken and cut into bite-sized pieces; set aside. Bring broth to a boil. Combine flour and salt together. Add milk, stirring with a fork, until it forms a firm dough. Pat out on a floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness. Pinch off and drop into boiling broth, gently stirring after each addition. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in chicken and serve immediately.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°
and	then
arrange apples in greased square pan (8 x
x
2-inch).
Mix
remaining
ingredients; sprinkle over apples.
Bake	until topping is golden brown and apples are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat with onion; add jar of taco sauce.
Set aside.
Meanwhile, have flour tortillas at room temperature or warm in microwave just enough to roll and not fall apart.
Combine 2 cans of soup, sour cream, "Jack" cheese and chilies; set aside. Spread flour tortillas on counter, filling center with meat mixture.
Using 8-inch tortillas you can make 30 to 40 enchiladas. Roll each of these up and secure with a toothpick.
Line enchiladas side by side, close together, in a baking dish or pan. Pour sauce over enchiladas.
Warm in oven (covered) at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with Colby cheese.

title: italian lasagna(microwave)
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain and set aside. Crumble ground beef into 2-quart casserole dish; add onions and microwave 11 to 12 minutes or until meat is set.
Stir to break meat into pieces; drain.
Stir in garlic, tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar, salt, parsley, basil and oregano; mix well.

Assemble in two 2 or 3-quart glass baking dish by layering 1/3 of noodles, 1/3 of meat sauce and 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese between the 2 pans. Repeat with next layer of noodles and meat and cheese until all used up.
Microwave bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes or until bubbly in center.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand condensed milk and continue to beat while adding lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with one of the toppings.
Chill for 1 hour before cutting.

title: broccoli soup(microwave)
directions: In a large, glass bowl, melt butter and cook 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Carefully blend in flour.
Gradually add broth, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
Cook on Medium 3 to 5 minutes or until soup begins to thicken.
Add thawed broccoli and return to Medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Soup is ready to serve.
Serves 4.

title: new orleans red beans and rice
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, simmer first five ingredients, uncovered.
(Important:
Do not soak beans.)
Saute celery, onions and garlic in oil until transparent.
Add these and smoked sausage, bay leaves and salt and pepper.
Continue to cook until beans are soft and creamy, approximately 2 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaves and add parsley before serving.
For additional thickness, cook longer. Serve over rice.

title: sandy's chicken curry
directions: Put chicken, stock, ginger and salt in a pan; simmer for about 30 minutes.
Heat oil in a small skillet; saute onions until golden.
Blend in garlic, peanut butter, curry powder and milk. Cook mixture over low heat for about 4 minutes.
Mix the flour and a small amount of water together until smooth.
Remove chicken pieces from stock; add flour mixture to stock.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Pour onion mixture into sauce and blend well.
Stir in the lemon juice and remaining seasonings.
Add chicken pieces to the sauce and heat through gently.

title: cranberry nut jello mold
directions: You will need 1 mold sprayed with Pam or buttered.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Season brisket with salt, pepper, garlic and onions.
Pour marinade over brisket and let stand overnight.
Cover and bake at 250° for 8 hours.

title: berry mandarin salad
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients and microwave on high for 1-1/2 to 2 minutes; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Whisk in oil. Cover and refrigerate until serving.
In a salad bowl, combine the remaining ingredients and drizzle with the dressing and serve. Yield: 12-14 servings.

title: home-made sauerkraut
directions: Mix salt and cabbage and place in large earthen jar.
If more water or brine is needed, use 2 tablespoons of salt to each quart of water.
Place in jars and seal.
After 6 weeks, can be processed 15 minutes in water bath.

title: onion-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 cup cracker crumbs in a greased 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
In a large skillet, melt 1/4 cup butter over medium heat.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Spoon onion over cracker crumbs.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugar and lemon rind.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour, baking powder and wine.
Pat dough into greased jelly roll pan, reserving some for top.
Cover with jelly or jam.
Crisscross with rolls of remaining dough.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: texas pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and cool; mix in sugar and eggs until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until evenly mixed.
Pour into an unbaked 10-inch pie shell. Bake for 1 hour.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except seasoned dressing mix. Top mixture with seasoned dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cap'n crunch treats
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and marshmallows together; mix with cereal.
Press in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chocolate bars, covering the top.
Place in warm oven (250°) until softened. Spread with knife.
Sprinkle with nuts, if you want.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
Salt and pepper to taste. This should take 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover. Cook over kerosene fire for 4 weeks at 465°.
Serves 3,800 people. If more than 3,800 people are expected, add 2 rabbits, but do so only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and spoon into a tightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside. Combine soups, 1/2 cup cheese, milk, mayonnaise, eggs and red pepper.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over broccoli.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add chicken and brown.
Add soup, water and vegetable combination. Heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 4.
Prep. Time:
10 minutes.
Cook Time:
20 minutes.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: 2 flavor fudge
directions: Combine in saucepan, brown sugar, granulated sugar, evaporated milk and butter or margarine.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add marshmallow cream, butterscotch and semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Blend in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Place chops in baking dish and season to taste.
Mix all ingredients together and pour or spread over chops.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: creamy peanut patties
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oleo and vanilla.
Boil 7 minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla; beat by hand to right consistency. Drop or pour out on buttered cookie sheet and break apart.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix together carrots, coconut and raisins.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frankfurter spaghetti casserole
directions: In skillet, cook bell pepper and onion in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, oregano, salt, pepper, then water.
Add milk, Worcestershire and cheese.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Cut frankfurters into pennies and add them with spaghetti to sauce.
Put into greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until almost dry. Northern beans work best.

title: yellow squash pickles
directions: Wash squash and cut into thin slices.
Peel onions into thin slices (very thin).
Cover squash and onions with water and add salt.
Let stand 2 hours and drain.
Add to the following mixture and heat.

title: fruit slush
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and freeze in shallow container.
Serve while still slushy.

title: broccoli tuna roll-ups
directions: Combine mushroom soup and milk; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients except the cheese together with 3/4 cup soup mixture. Divide tuna mixture evenly on the tortillas, roll up and place seam down in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir 1 chopped tomato or mild picante sauce into the remaining soup mixture and pour over the roll-ups.
Bake, covered, 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove the cover and top center of tortillas with the cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes until cheese melts.
If you wish to use more shredded cheese, you can put some in the tuna mixture.

title: macaroni hawaiian salad
directions: Drain fruit and save juice.
Cook macaroni in salt water until tender; rinse and drain.
Mix sugar, eggs, flour, salt and juice. Cook until slightly thick.
Put macaroni in bowl with cover.
Pour hot sauce over macaroni; put cover on and refrigerate overnight. Fold in fruit and Cool Whip in morning.

title: deviled turkey bonbons
directions: Combine turkey and 1/2 cup nuts.
Add remaining ingredients except remaining nuts; mix well.
Shape into small balls and roll in remaining chopped nuts.
Chill until serving time.

title: scallops provencal
directions: Melt butter in large skillet and saute garlic over medium heat about 3 minutes.
Add wine and simmer 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, parsley, salt and pepper and simmer 10 to 12 minutes until very thick.
Add scallops to pan and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until scallops are opaque.
Do not overcook.
In small bowl, mix bread crumbs and Parmesan.
Transfer scallops to ovensafe pan and sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Lightly brown under the broiler. Serve immediately.

title: coconut or egg custard pie
directions: Dump all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Pour into greased pie plate and set aside for 5 minutes. Do not stir.
For coconut pie, add 1 cup sprinkled on the top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soak bread crumbs in milk for 10 minutes.
Blend salmon in the rest of the ingredients, except egg whites.
Fold in salmon to egg whites.
Put in greased loaf pan. Bake 45 minutes.

title: rice and peaches
directions: Cook rice as on package; drain peaches and reserve 1/2 cup of the liquid and 12 peach slices.
Drain remaining peaches.
Mix drained peaches, sugar, lemon juice, margarine and spices into hot cooked rice.
Mix well; simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour whipped topping over rice.
Arrange peach slices on top and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: abaco nocha "concrete"
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; process just until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides. Mixture will be thick.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: banana spice drops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend margarine, sugar, eggs and bananas.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet which has been greased.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: apple chunk cake
directions: Cook the apples in the molasses and water until soft.
Add the shortening and cool. Add the sugar and stir well. Sift the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Mix dry ingredients into the first mixture.
Add the vanilla.
Raisins or nuts may also be added.
Bake in a 325° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
Test occasionally.
May serve with whipped cream or serve it up warm from the oven.

title: tangy broccoli salad
directions: Mix dressing, sugar and vinegar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: goulash
directions: Cook the onion until yellow in the margarine. Add and cook until brown the ground beef.
Add the peeled tomatoes, celery, bell pepper, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 hour. Cook the macaroni and drain. Stir into meat mixture and enjoy.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl at low speed of electric mixer until blended.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup, butter, vanilla and salt with spoon until blended.
Stir in nuts, chocolate chips and bourbon. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.
Cover edge with foil, if necessary, to prevent overbrowning.
Cool to room temperature before serving. Refrigerate leftover pie.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients and add bananas.
Pour over flour mixture and stir to mix.
Drop tablespoonful of batter onto greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: bagel dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in crock pot. Serve with cut up bagels or crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directions on package say (small amount of salt in water).
Combine soup, cheese, mayonnaise, onions and eggs.
Put broccoli in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch casserole and pour other ingredients over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs or croutons.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: helen's broccoli-onion deluxe
directions: Cook
broccoli	according
to
directions; drain.
Cook onion in boiling, salted water until tender, about 10 minutes; drain.

title: mexicano
directions: Line a large casserole with tortillas.
Layer meat, onions, beans and cheese, then cover with a layer of tortillas.
Spread the soup over the top, then pour tomatoes over soup.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: taco soup
directions: Fry hamburger and drain add onion and taco seasoning.
In a big pot add all other ingredients with juice.
Heat.
Add the meat, stir and simmer to let flavors blend.
(I use 2 cans of pinto beans instead of kidney beans, and an extra can of corn instead of hominy.)
Top with Fritos and shredded cheese.
Makes a lot but you can freeze.

title: birthday pie
directions: So named because sons used to (and still do) at times request in lieu of cake!

title: pots de creme
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Run blender for 1 minute on low speed.
Pour equally among 6 small ramekins.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Top with whipping cream.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell for 8 minutes. Remove and reduce temperature to 350°.
In a small pan, cook onion in margarine until tender.
In medium bowl, beat together eggs, milk and bouillon.
Toss together cheese and flour; add to egg mixture along with remaining ingredients.
Turn into pastry shell.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt the butter or margarine and marshmallows together. Chop up fruit and nuts. Crush graham crackers. Mix fruit, nuts, graham crackers, coconut and raisins. Add melted butter and marshmallows. Mix well. Press down well into 2 tube or Bundt pans (ungreased). Let stand for about an hour. Run hot water over the bottom of the pan until the cake comes out.

title: artichoke salad dressing
directions: In a saucepan combine oil, vinegar, water, celery seed, salt, pepper, onion, sugar and garlic.
Bring mixture to boil. Add artichoke
hearts.
Cook
until
tender,
3 to 5 minutes. Cool; stir
in
pimiento.
Chill
until serving time.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Mix
favorite
green salad and add artichoke
mixture. Toss
with
enough
of
the reserved marinade (about 1/4 cup) to coat greens.

title: knorr vegetable dip
directions: Mix soup mix and sour cream.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Serve with all kinds of bite-size vegetables.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in
jelly roll pan or cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix flour and milk together. Cook until thick and cool completely.
Cream sugar, shortening, vanilla and softened margarine together until smooth.
Spread on cooled cake and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar; add eggs, flour, sour cream, vanilla, baking
powder, soda and salt and mix well.
Pour 1/2 of batter
into
greased tube pan.
Sprinkle topping of cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts
or
dates
on top of batter and top with remaining batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cake will fall slightly when removed from oven.

title: oven-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger and onion and put in casserole.
Layer in potatoes,
then
top
with	soup which has been mixed with milk. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients. Drop into greased and floured muffin tins. Bake at 400° until golden brown. Makes 12 muffins.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Mix the flour, butter, brown sugar and pecans together. Crumble on a rimmed cookie sheet and brown in oven; set aside. Beat egg whites; add sugar, gradually, while continuing to beat until stiffens.
Then stir in the thawed strawberries mixed with lemon juice.
Whip the cream until stiff and fold into strawberry mixture.
Sprinkle all but 1/4 cup of pecan mixture in bottom of a 9 x 12 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Drop strawberry mixture on top by spoonfuls and gently spread until even.
Sprinkle remaining pecan mixture on top.
Freeze.
Will keep two weeks in freezer.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over sliced cucumbers; let stand for 2 hours. Drain off water.
Pour sugar and vinegar over pickles; let stand for 10 minutes.
Stir and place cucumbers in containers and freeze.
(Bags work great.) After 2 days, pickles are ready to eat.
Thaw at room temperature.
After completely thawed, store in refrigerator.

title: turkey tenderloin almandine
directions: Melt margarine in a nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add turkey and brown evenly on both sides.
Add lemon rind and juice. Cover and continue to cook 15 minutes or until turkey is no longer pink, turning once.
Transfer turkey tenderloins to small serving platter and keep warm.
Add almonds to skillet and saute until lightly browned.
Pour almond mixture over tenderloins and cut in half to serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the oats, flour, brown sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg until smooth.
In another bowl, combine the buttermilk, oil, mashed banana and egg.
Stir the liquid ingredients into the dry ingredients all at once, stirring just until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in the dates.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix together oleo, cake mix and coconut until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Place apples on crust.
Sprinkle on sugar and cinnamon.
Mix together sour cream and beaten egg.
Drizzle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: kolaches
directions: Mix
warm
water, 2 teaspoons of sugar and yeast; cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Cover; let rise 20 minutes.
Add milk, salt, eggs, 1 3/4 cups sugar, oleo and 4 cups flour.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in eggs and bread crumbs and brown in oil.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Add Ragu sauce and top with the rest of the cheeses. Bake 30 minutes.

title: baked spinach dip(serves 8 to 10)
directions: In medium bowl, mix all ingredients together and pour into ovenproof dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with pita chips, bagel chips or crackers.

title: greek cookies(kourabiedes)
directions: Beat butter for 1/2 hour, until creamy.
Add egg, vanilla and sugar; beat.
Shape cookies and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Put hot cookies on wax paper and sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.
May have to coat twice.

title: pecan cream cheese pie
directions: Add remaining teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well and pour over 1st mixture.
Line edge of pie crust with foil.
Bake for 20 minutes. Remove foil and bake 15 to 20 minutes more or until knife inserted one-inch from edge comes out clean.

title: cajun chow mein
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pepperoni pasta casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper; drain.
Add pepperoni, tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and mushrooms; mix well and heat.
Cook pasta; drain and add to hamburger mixture.
Heat until bubbly.
Shred or thinly slice the cheeses.
Place 1/2 hamburger mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese over the hamburger mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Excellent with salad and garlic bread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, then put Cheddar cheese on top and melt.

title: baked bean medley
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook ground beef and onion until onion is tender.
Drain.
In a colander, drain one can of pork and beans, kidney beans, red beans and lima beans.
To the Dutch oven, add all of the beans and all other ingredients.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven about 1 hour or until heated through.
Serves 24.

title: individual cheesecake
directions: Mix and cream first 3 ingredients together well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Place a vanilla wafer on bottom of cupcake holders and fill halfway up with mixture.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool completely and top with blueberry or cherry pie filling.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over corn mixture.
Mix well.
Cover; store in refrigerator overnight. Drain before serving.
Keeps several days under refrigeration.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, Karo and salt together and boil on top of stove 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda.
Add peanuts, if using. Pour mixture over corn.
Stir with spoon to coat corn.
Pour into shallow pans and bake for 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes. When done, let cool, then break up into pieces.
Store in tight containers.

title: skillet loaf
directions: Mix ground chuck, oats, onions, salt, pepper, egg, A. 1. sauce and 1/2 can mushroom soup in a bowl by hand.

title: hoppel poppel
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and pour into shallow, buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until set. Cut into 12 pieces.
Very good for a brunch or lunch.

title: fruit and cheese spread
directions: Combine and chill.
Serve on rye bread square.

title: galveston gumbo
directions: Saute okra in shortening about 10 minutes or until okra appears dry, stirring constantly.
Add onion, garlic, salt, pepper and shrimp.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add water, tomatoes and bay leaves.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Add liquid hot pepper sauce.
Place 1/4 cup rice in bottom of 6 bowls; fill with gumbo.
Serves 6.
tags: drops of liquid hot pepper sauce

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand and lemon juice.
Add fruit and nuts to this.
Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: zucchini chow chow
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and let set overnight (covered).
I use food processor for chopping.
Next morning, rinse well with cold water and drain real good (I use nylon net). Press firmly to get water out.
This is important.
After thoroughly draining, put in pan the vinegar, sugar, nutmeg, turmeric, mustard, cornstarch and celery seed.
Bring to boil; simmer 30 minutes.
Put in prepared jars and seal.
Real good.

title: french-fried shrimp
directions: Combine eggs and salt.
Combine flour, dry bread crumbs and paprika.
Dip each shrimp in egg, then
roll in crumb mixture. Fry in a basket in deep fat at 350° for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve with ketchup or tartar sauce.

title: tasty frankfurters
directions: Combine butter, soy sauce and maple syrup in a frying pan. Score franks or cut into pieces and add to simmering sauce.
Stir until meat is coated, then simmer until sauce is dark and thick. The longer these are simmered, the better they are.

title: cheesecake creme dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme, mixing until well blended.
Stir in lemon rind and cinnamon or ginger. Serve as a dip with chunks of fresh fruit or cubes of pound cake. Makes about 2 cups.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Wash celery. Cut into 3-inch strips.
In mixing bowl, blend cheeses, peppers and chili powder.
Stuff celery.
Garnish with paprika.

title: easy marshmallow strawberry pie
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk in top of double boiler.
Let cool.
Fold in whipped cream and strawberries.
Pour into cool cooked pie crust or crumb crust.
Cool for several hours.
Serve with whipped cream and top each slice with a strawberry.
Can make a day ahead.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients, except food coloring, on medium speed until frosting is smooth and of desired consistency.
If necessary, stir in additional milk, 1 teaspoon at a time.
Tint with desired food coloring.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix boiled pasta with 1/2 of Italian dressing and the Salad Supreme.
Let marinate overnight.
Next day, add the remaining ingredients and Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let bread rise according to directions on package.
Roll out dough into a square.
Lay down 1 layer of Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Lay down rest of ingredients.
Start at one end and roll up dough.
Tuck and smooth ends so ingredients will not ooze out.
Brush loaf with melted butter and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tea syrup
directions: Boil all ingredients for 3 minutes to form syrup mixture. Put 1 Tbsp. of mixture into glass and fill with water and ice. Stir well.

title: ship wreck hot dish
directions: Season each layer and cook uncovered for 2 hours at 350°.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Put blueberries and pineapple in baking dish. Sprinkle cake mix over top. Slice oleo on top of cake mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: dip surprise
directions: Chop 1 onion into small pieces; drain your choice of meat. Mix with cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together and serve on crackers.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Blend oil, orange juice, vinegar and seasonings; add to chicken mixture.
Chill 1 hour. Drain.
Add mayonnaise; mix well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sticky, but good!
directions: Skin chicken first.
Bake chicken in a 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Drain.
Return chicken to casserole.
In a separate bowl, mix honey, jelly and seasoning.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with dates.
Bake for 15 minutes, after lowering temperature to 350°.

title: baked crab imperial
directions: Gently combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.
In saucepan combine last 4 ingredients.
Place crab meat in individual baking dishes.
Pour sauce over crab meat.
Do not stir.
Bake in oven at 400° to 425° for 20 minutes.
Cheese is optional.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: Cut leeks lengthwise in half to wash them good.
Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Heat the oil heavy skillet and brown chops well on both sides.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Add onion to skillet and brown well.
Return pork chops to pan and simmer for 15 minutes on each side.
Meanwhile, wash leeks well and cut into slices lengthwise.
Melt the butter in a sauce pan. Add leeks and brown lightly.
Stir in green pepper and apples. Season with paprika. Add salt and pepper to taste.	Cover and simmer on low heat for 20 minutes. Serve the vegetables on the side with the pork chops.

title: em's roasted chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Sprinkle inside and out with spice mixture.
Stuff vegetables in cavity; add remainder around chicken in pot and place sliced fruits on top of bird.
Add wine, cover pan and roast in 350° oven until done, approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Allow to stand 10 or 15 minutes.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: spider
directions: Spread peanut butter on one cracker.
Put 4 pretzels on each side.
Add fangs.
(Use small pieces of pretzel sticks.)
Put the other cracker on top.
Attach the raisin eyes with a little peanut butter.
Enjoy the spider!

title: pina colada coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan. While cake is still warm, punch holes all in cake. Mix sweetened condensed milk, cream of coconut and 1/4 frozen coconut and pour over cake. Put Saran Wrap over cake and freeze overnight. Next morning take out of freezer and put Cool Whip on cake and the rest of the frozen coconut. Keep in refrigerator.

title: grilled tuna
directions: Place tuna steaks in shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over tuna.
Refrigerate 45 minutes, turning once.
Grill steaks over moderately hot coals 5 to 6 minutes per side, depending on thickness.
Steaks are done when slightly pink in center.

title: mrs. a. p. (hilda) nelson's parfait
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water; add lemon juice.
Cool slightly (just beginning to congeal).
Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites stiff and add 1/4 cup sugar slowly.
Beat egg yolks with beater and 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat whites and yolks together and fold into slightly set jello mixture.

title: sweet dill refrigerator pickles
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, water and salt. Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.

title: tuna cheesie
directions: Turn oven temperature to broil. Peel onion and chop very fine. Wash celery and chop until fine. Drain tuna. Combine with onion and celery in small bowl. Sprinkle with pepper.
Add mayonnaise and mix.
Toast English muffins, cut in half first.
Spread tuna mixture on muffin.
Place tomato slice on tuna. Top with cheese. Put on cookie sheet. Broil 5-inches from heat for 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts and starts to brown.

title: soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil 8-inch round baking dish.
Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Add buttermilk, egg and oil.
Stir with fork until ingredients are moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from dish.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Beat eggs one at a time.
In a separate bowl, mix together butter, flour and sugar.
Add frosting mix and nuts.
By hand, stir into egg mixture.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes in a Bundt or tube pan at 350° until done.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: orange delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows in boiling water; set in refrigerator.
Cream the cream cheese; add sugar.
Blend in Cool Whip until thick.
Add thickened Jell-O, pineapple and pecans. Pour into mold and chill.
Serve as a sweet salad or dessert.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat in order given.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Makes approximately 3 medium pans.
Bake for 50 minutes, but check often.
Serve with cream cheese.

title: ranch beans
directions: Cook pinto beans until tender.
Add chili, tomatoes and chopped onion.
Continue to cook until onion is tender.
Season to taste.

title: fruit salad
directions: Take pineapple juice and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add jello pudding.
Cook until clear and thick.
Let cool (room temperature). Add all fruit, except bananas, and mix.
Add bananas before serving. Looks pretty when served in a glass bowl.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add cold water.
Cool until it begins to set, then add chopped lettuce.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm.
This is so simple I very seldom remember to make it.
Excellent to serve with meat dishes because it is so refreshing.

title: cheesy hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion and peppers in butter.
Add to mixed hominy, soup, chili powder and shredded cheese.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Place 1 pastry round into a greased or nonstick pie pan. Combine apple juice and cornstarch in a large saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Add margarine and spices. Mix well and stir in apples. Spoon mixture into pie crust. Place remaining crust on top; cut slits in top crust. Fold edges and flute. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cut shrimp in small pieces. Combine all ingredients. Serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: uncle ben's chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Add remaining ingredients and place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, for 45 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 4.

title: bermuda casserole
directions: Parboil onions for 10 minutes.
Place in buttered casserole dish, layered with bread and cheese.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and pepper; pour over top layer.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: mock stuffed baked lobster
directions: Place 1/4 pound butter in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt butter in pan. Cut haddock fillets into 1-inch pieces into pan.
In a bowl, crush crackers and add salt, pepper, paprika, grated cheese and a tablespoon of melted butter.
Toss to mix and cover fish chunks with this mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy; this is delicious.

title: pancake mix
directions: Preheat skillet or griddle over medium heat. Spray with non-stick cooking spray.

title: tailgate ham sandwiches
directions: Slice rolls all in one piece (take the top off in one piece). Soften butter and spread on both sides of bread.
Mix poppy seed, Worcestershire, onion and mustard.
Spread this mixture on both sides of the bread.
Put ham on bottom, then cheese and then put top back on.
Cut before eating.
Heat at 400° for 15 minutes. This is great for a snack, supper or a group of kids!!

title: cheese 'n potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes thinly.
Layer in greased 2-quart casserole half of potato slices, seasonings, grated cheese and soup.
Dot with half of margarine; make a second layer of potatoes, seasonings and soup.
Dot with remaining butter.
Rinse soup can with milk; pour over top of casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover.
Sprinkle on 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add half a can of cream of mushroom soup.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Fill the tortillas with the chicken/cheese mixture; sprinkle some hot sauce on top and roll up.
Place, seam side down, in the prepared baking dish.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil until done first 4 ingredients.
Then stir in margarine and thickening.
If too thick, add milk to thin.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep dish.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and milk.
Pour over margarine.
Place peaches on top of batter.
Bake in oven at 350° until crust is golden brown and has raised over peaches.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease
casserole
dish
generously.
Place
layer
of crackers in dish.
Put asparagus and eggs in next layer. Slice butter and put on top.
Sprinkle red pepper or paprika on top. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Brown green pepper, onion and mushrooms in 3 tablespoons margarine. Cook until tender. Add mushroom soup, half and half, Cheddar cheese, wine, cooked spaghetti and turkey.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° until hot.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes and cook until done. Add 1 1/2 cups sugar, vanilla and lemon juice. Pour into casserole dish. Combine melted butter, milk, remaining sugar and flour in a medium bowl and mix well. Pour over sweet potatoes and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: french doughnuts
directions: Cream butter, sugar and 1 egg at a time; cream thoroughly. Add salt and vanilla; stir in alternately part of milk and 2 cups of flour.
Mix baking powder in third cup of flour; continue milk and flour until a thick smooth batter.
Deep fry in at least 2 inches of hot fat (400°).
Self turning, done on second turn. (First batter, push off by finger.)

title: marinated chuck steak
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Pour marinade over the chuck steak.
Chill overnight, then broil or grill steak.
Serves 4. Preparation:
10 minutes.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in blender and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: beef tips
directions: Sprinkle tenderizer, pepper and thyme on beef.
Stir and place in baking pan and cook at 400° 1 hour to brown, turning once while browning.
Mix soups and water and stir in Kitchen Bouquet, onions and parsley.
Pour over meat; stir and return to oven.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Heat all three ingredients together in a large pan or crock-pot.
Add water as needed if mixture is too thick.
Serve with nachos.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Add evaporated milk and cheese; mix together.
Add tuna and peas; mix all together.
Bake in oven 20 minutes at 350°.

title: blender pie
directions: Blend 1 minute and pour in well-greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Add nutmeg on top, if desired.
Makes own crust.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in Italian dressing for 1 to 4 hours. Roll in crushed corn flake crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Mix beef with milk and salt.
Divide in 5 pieces.
Flatten each piece to form a six-inch circle.
Spoon 1/4 cup of stuffing in the center of each.
Draw the edges over stuffing and seal.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, vinegar and sugar and add to broccoli and cauliflower.
Add bacon.
Let stand in refrigerator to blend.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Salt and pepper, using hot pepper.
Cook on low heat for a long time.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine peas, beans, corn, celery and pimento.
In saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: clabber girl biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Work in shortening with fingertips to mix thoroughly.
Add sufficient milk, while stirring vigorously, to make a soft dough.
Lightly roll or pat on floured board to about 3/4-inch thickness. Cut with floured biscuit cutter and place on greased baking pan.
Bake in hot oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 14 biscuits 2 inches in size.

title: pheasant deluxe
directions: Put rice in large casserole.
Add soups, wine and dry soup mix; let stand for 2 hours.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Brown pheasant pieces in butter.
Place on top of baked rice mixture. Return to oven and bake, covered, for 2 hours at 325°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oklahoma scramble
directions: Combine all vegetables together.
Fry in grease as you would fried potatoes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine and bring to a good boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Take off heat and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients, then immediately pour out in large buttered pan.

title: toll oat cookies
directions: Cream margarine. Add sugars, eggs, water and vanilla. Sift flour and soda together. Add to creamed mixture and blend thoroughly. Add oats chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in moderate oven (375°) for about 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Set aside. In bowl, mix self-rising flour, sugar and milk. Mix well and pour in the pan of melted margarine and stir. Pour the can of sliced peaches into the mixture. Bake in preheated oven at 375° to 400° until golden brown.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large boiler 3/4 full of water, boil 8 lasagna noodles; let boil for 20 minutes.
In large skillet, brown onion, ground beef and Italian sausage.
Add pepper and salt.
Drain off all the oil from the meat.
Add 1/2 cup of wine and the oregano.
Turn heat on low; let simmer for 10 minutes.
Add can of whole tomatoes and sauce; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: honey coconut loaf
directions: Beat together water, eggs, vegetable oil, honey and sugar. Mix flour with baking soda, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
Add gradually to liquid mixture, stirring just to blend.
Fold in citron and coconut. Spoon into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean. Cool on rack in pan 10 minutes.
Carefully remove from pan and cool on rack. Wrap cooled loaf in aluminum foil and store overnight before cutting.

title: crispy caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in a large, well-greased pan.
In a large heavy saucepan, melt butter; stir in next 3 ingredients and boil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour syrup over popcorn, mixing well.
Place popcorn on well-greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
When cool enough to handle, separate kernels.
Store tightly covered.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, salt, sugar, and baking soda.
Mix the pumpkin, oil, eggs, 1/4 cup water and the spices together, then combine with the dry ingredients; do not mix too thoroughly.
Stir in the nuts.
Pour into a well-buttered 9-inch by 5-inch by 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean.
Turn out of pan and cool on a rack. Makes 1 loaf.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix sugar and egg yolks.
Add butter and dates and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Make into balls and roll in coconut.

title: fried chicken(low-calorie)
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 375° (for crisp chicken, preheat to 425°).
Cut chicken into serving size pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Melt butter or vegetable oil in skillet.
Dip chicken into seasoned flour.
Place in skillet and cook until chicken is golden brown on all sides.
Add water.
Cover skillet, lower temperature to 250°.
Continue cooking for about 45 minutes.

title: fresh basil cheese spread
directions: Process with the knife blade until smooth.
(May be made in blender in small batches.)
Makes 3 1/2 cups.
Use this on spaghetti.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch until clear; add Jell-O. Place fresh fruit in pie crust.
Pour mixture over fruit.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add the milk, vanilla and salt to chocolate.
Then add the melted butter.
Mix in and blend well the powdered sugar.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in hot oil until tender.
(If garlic clove is used, cook with vegetables; if powder is used, mix with dry ingredients.) Stir in flour, salt, sugar and pepper which have been mixed together.
Add water; simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, vinegar and bay leaves. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot rice.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Cut green cabbage or shred with knife.
Heat oil in skillet. Add cabbage, garlic and peppers.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Then add onions and salt.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crumby, crumb cake
directions: Follow directions on box; bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add crumb mixture to top; bake 20 minutes longer.

title: denver omelet
directions: Beat eggs and milk in small bowl.
Chop tomato, ham, green pepper and cheese in small chunks.
(Put in separate bowl.)
Melt butter into skillet.
Pour eggs into skillet like a pancake.
Cook on one side.
Turn over quickly.
Add other ingredients to one side.
Fold egg in half and cook on one side.
Turn over and cook on other side.

title: mud slide cake
directions: Melt butter and mix with crumbs and sugar; press into a long cake pan.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Add Jell-O.
Cool until thick.
Soften
cream
cheese
with milk.
Prepare Dream Whip. Fold all together and cool.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage together; drain off fat. Add Velveeta cheese, ground beef, sausage, cream of mushroom soup (do not add water to soup) and Ro-Tel tomatoes to a 6-quart crock-pot. Stir until cheese is melted, then serve with tortilla chips.

title: crispy chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix Bisquick and pepper in large plastic bag.
Stir chicken into eggs; remove chicken with slotted spoon and place in bag with baking mix.
Shake bag until chicken is coated; remove chicken from bag.

title: fruit slush
directions: Put fruit in large bowl.
Add orange juice and 12 ounces water.
Add the 3 cups water and 2 cups sugar after bringing to a boil; mix well.
Freeze for 24 hours, stirring every 4 hours.

title: polly's fruit "pizza"
directions: Press dough into a cookie sheet with sides.
Cold dough is easier to work with.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool. Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cooked crust.
In a saucepan over medium heat, cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly, 1/2 cup sugar, the orange and lemon juice and the cornstarch.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Place a variety of sliced fresh fruit such as kiwi, strawberries, peaches, grapes, etc. over the crust.
Cover with the fruit juice mixture.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar until smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and stir into egg mixture.
Add nuts, apple and vanilla flavoring.

title: chocolate macaroon bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine cracker crumbs, sugar, cocoa and butter and press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes.

title: rise 'n shine shake
directions: Combine all in a blender.
Blend until smooth. Pour in glasses.

title: scripture cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and allspice (set aside).
Cream your butter and sugar.
Add honey and eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Combine fruit and nuts in small bowl.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the flour mixture over the fruit and nuts.
Add remaining flour mixture to creamed sugar and butter.
Alternate with milk.
Stir in fruit and nuts.

title: lavender surprise
directions: Mix cottage cheese with dry Jell-O.
Use electric mixer.
Add pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.
I use an 8 x 11-inch Pyrex pan for this.
To serve, cut in squares and put on lettuce.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease and flour large tube or Bundt pan.
Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, 3 at a time and alternate with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: turkey dressing for 50
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions and celery and saute until tender.
Crumble bread.
Add seasonings, cooked onions and celery. Mix together.
Add liquid and eggs and mix well.
Bake in greased pans at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.
(I mix mine up the night before as this improves flavor.
Store in refrigerator.) Serves 50.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken 15 to 20 minutes.
Season chicken with salt. Saute onion.
Add soups and broth to onion.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and chicken to soup mix.
Bring to boil.

title: trinity cabbage salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand to marinate.

title: quick taco pie
directions: Brown meat.
Add taco seasoning, water and olives.
Simmer. Press biscuits into 9-inch pie plate to form the crust.
Put 1 cup corn chips on bottom of crust.
Add meat, then sour cream and cheese.
Top with remaining corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with lettuce, onions, tomatoes and taco sauce.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate about 2 days before using.

title: pumpkin cookie bars
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Add butter, mix until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: mixed greens
directions: Cook salt pork 30 minutes in 6 or 7 cups water. Trim away any bruised or blemished spots on greens with a sharp knife. Wash the leaves in several changes of cold running water to remove all traces of dirt or sand. Cut up and combine the greens in Dutch oven with remaining ingredients, including salt pork and water. Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook until done or tender, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chip chopped ham
directions: Mix all together in a casserole bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour with cover on and then for the last 10 minutes with cover off.

title: fresh apple cake(this cake is even better after 2 days.)
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add juice and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix with sugar and egg mixture.
Add apples, pecans and coconut.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Leave cake in pan and pour icing over while hot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in pan of water. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix bread, seasoning and mayonnaise.
Add crabmeat; mix gently but thoroughly.
If too dry add more mayonnaise.
Cook cakes in frypan until brown, 5 minutes or deep fry.
Makes 6 crab cakes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Skin chicken and cut into parts.
Salt, pepper and garlic the chicken.
Brown in skillet in butter.
(Margarine makes chicken stick.)
Add onion and saute.
Pour rice over chicken.
Put 2 cups water over all.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in can of cream of chicken soup and simmer 15 more minutes.

title: english muffin crab and cheese
directions: Mix ingredients together, except muffins.
Spread mixture on muffin halves.
Cut topped muffin halves in quarters.
Freeze. (These can be frozen indefinitely.)

title: chili cheese spread
directions: Fill tortilla with cheese; melt in microwave for 45 seconds. Top with sauce.

title: spinach salad
directions: Rinse spinach leaves well.
Place them on paper towels to drain excess water.
Break away the stem. Break leaves into a salad bowl.
Add chopped boiled eggs and bacon bits.
Take sliced onion and take apart to have onion rings.
Toss everything together.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, top with Ranch dressing and croutons.

title: pasta salad supreme
directions: The night before, cook linguine and refrigerate.
Mix Salad Supreme and Italian dressing; refrigerate overnight.
Chop veggies; add to both linguine and salad dressing.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar.
Add sugar slowly after egg
whites
get
foamy.
Beat
egg
yolks	until lemon colored. Add
condensed milk; mix well.
Add lime juice; beat until blended.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Mix together and place in freezer.
Freeze for 12 hours and serve.
You can refreeze the leftover until it's gone.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat together eggs, salt, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Line casserole dish with bread.
Brown sausage.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Add sausage.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven fried eggplant
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix seasoned crumbs and salt.
Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip slices into egg.
Then coat with crumbs.
Arrange in pan.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Turn and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Add butter, melted in dressing.
Put a layer of dressing in dish, layer of chicken, add soup, then rest of dressing mix.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: old-fashion pound cake
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, butter, shortening and vanilla.
Cream all together.
Add flour and milk and beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until when toothpick is stuck in center comes out clean.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and slice.
Use enough corn oil to cover bottom of frypan.
Put in potatoes, using medium heat.
Add sugars.
Cover with lid until potatoes are tender.
Uncover and let syrup thicken.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and butter in bowl 1 to 2 minutes on High.
Stir every 30 seconds.
Remove from microwave and stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Spread evenly in the crust. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Chocolate will be firm.

title: cole slaw
directions: Wash and chop cabbage.
Mix in all ingredients well. Refrigerate.

title: angel squares
directions: Grease bottom only of pan.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until soft mound forms.
Add 1 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add vanilla and hot milk.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour over egg whites; by hand, fold in carefully just until well combined.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until top springs back.
Cool.
Frost and drizzle with chocolate glaze.
Serve in squares.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Put in large bowl.
Add mushrooms, mayo, pimento, mushroom soup, onions and bell pepper; mix thoroughly.
Place in baking dish.
Top with cheese, Ritz crackers and Parmesan.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can freeze for a short time.
I usually double this recipe when I take it to church or a family gathering.

title: cheesy baked chicken
directions: Melt margarine.
Dip each chicken breast in margarine.
Mix all other ingredients together and coat each breast.
Place in baking dish and drizzle remaining margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not cover and do not turn.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt and oregano.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch greased dish or pan, 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, 1/2 noodles, 1/2 cheese mixture, 1 cup sliced zucchini and repeat.
Top with remaining sauce; sprinkle rest of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Just before baking, pour the 1 cup water around edge; cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: grandma's pecan pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add beaten eggs and pecans. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes, depending on oven.

title: cranberry swirl cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, then add dry ingredients with sour cream.
Add flavoring.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Cut in Crisco and peanut butter until resembles coarse meal.
Blend in syrup and milk. Shape into rolls 2 inches in diameter; chill.
Slice 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Place half the slices on ungreased cookie sheet. Spread each with 1/2 teaspoon peanut butter.
Cover with remaining slices; seal edges with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, or until browned.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: sweet potato-ham casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Stir in water until smooth.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in 1 cup Pet milk and ham.
Pour into greased 2-quart round casserole.
Beat together potatoes, 2/3 cup Pet milk and salt. Drop by tablespoons over creamed ham.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until sweet potatoes are browned and creamed mixture is bubbly. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: paella
directions: Brown chops and chicken until done or almost done; set aside. In large roaster, brown onions, peppers and garlic to soft state in 1/2 cup olive oil.
Wash 3 cups rice in strainer until water is clear.

title: chicken huntington
directions: Cook chicken in deep water with chopped celery and onion. When chicken is tender, remove and bone.
Strain celery and onion from broth.
Cook noodles in broth and drain.
Mix chicken, noodles, portion of grated Velveeta cheese, celery, onion, 1/2 small jar pimentos, cut up, cream of mushroom soup and frozen peas.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan.
Put remaining grated cheese on top and cook, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese sticks
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour and cayenne pepper until mixed.
Cut in cheese and butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Using hands, work dough until mixture holds together.
Shape into a ball.

title: pecadillo
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add garlic and onion until transparent. Drain grease.
Add tomatoes, green pepper and raisins.
Season to taste.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add almonds and olives.
Serve over rice.

title: pork tender steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak and sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt over steak. Cut into pieces. Brown in small amount of oil or shortening. Place meat in bottom of casserole. Top with onions, then potatoes, ending with carrots. Spread tomato soup over top until covered. Cover with aluminum foil and bake in 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add nuts and apples.
Mix in flour, one cup at a time.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Beat yolks. Melt butter and stir in confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Then layer.
Pinch cake up in little pieces, then mixture over top.
Keep layering until all is gone.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds from peppers and grind, saving the pulp and juice. (A food processor is great for grinding everything for this.) Repeat with jalapeno.
Mix bell peppers, jalapeno, cider vinegar and sugar in a 4 x 6-quart saucepan and bring this to boil. Add Certo and bring to a boil, stirring for 1 minute.
Let stand for a minute. Skim off foam. Add food coloring.
Pour in jelly jars and seal. Good with cream cheese on Ritz crackers.

title: italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in Pyrex dish.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Dot with margarine, salt and pepper.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Layer in a large container, lettuce, broccoli, peas, bacon, Parmesan cheese, cauliflower, onions and tops and celery.
Mix together mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread over the top like icing.
Seal tight and chill several hours.
Toss before serving. Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and beef together.
Drain excess fat.
Add soup and Velveeta cheese.
Put in a crock-pot on low; stir as cheese melts.
Use with corn chips, nachos, potato chips or veggies.
You can use only half of meat to make it thinner if you want to.

title: applesauce cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Spread applesauce in 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of applesauce.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of the cake mix.
Add the pecans evenly on top of the brown sugar.
Lay the butter slices on top of the pecans. Bake uncovered at 300° for one hour.

title: southwestern salad
directions: Tear a head of lettuce into bite size pieces, then add tomatoes, sliced olives, shredded Cheddar cheese, black beans and onions. Combine salsa and Ranch dressing. Mix into salad.

title: sweet and sour beef
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Stir in onions, 1/2 cup water, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Blend cold water and cornstarch.
Use to thicken as desired.
Serve over rice.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mix.
Drop into a Bundt pan.
In a small saucepan, melt brown sugar and butter.
Pour over biscuits in the Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over biscuits.
Put pan in cold oven.
Turn on to 350° and bake 25 to 35 minutes.
Turn out of pan to serve.
Good for breakfast.

title: grape-nuts custard pudding
directions: Scald milk with small piece of butter added.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and cook in pan of hot water.
Bake in 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes out dry.

title: quick and delicious rolls
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, salt and boiling water.
Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup lukewarm water.
When shortening mixture is cooled to lukewarm, add dissolved yeast, beaten eggs and flour.
Beat with mixer on medium speed for 1 minute.
Place in greased bowl in refrigerator.
Leave overnight or until thoroughly chilled.
Knead very little using as little flour as possible.
Roll, cut and dip in melted margarine.
Let rise and bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: rarebit
directions: Melt oleo over low heat.
Add flour and salt.
Allow to cook a minute.
Remove pan from heat.
Slowly add, stirring constantly, milk.
Return to heat; cook until slightly thickened.
Add cheese. Cook over low heat until thick.
Serve over toast.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into balls about 1 1/2 inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
Combine Crisco and sugar, beat at medium speed until blended.
Beat in egg.
Blend in molasses. Combine
flour,
soda,
ginger
and
cinnamon.
Add
to mixture. Drop
round teaspoonful of dough in a dish of sugar. Roll.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: sunday chicken n' rice
directions: Saute onions, peppers and rice (brown) in skillet in oil.
In oblong baking dish, pour rice mixture in bottom, arrange chicken on top of rice.
Mix in separate bowl the water and cream of chicken soup.
Whisk until creamy.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Add salt. Bake during Sunday School on low (225°) for 2 hours.
Perfect meal, ready to eat!
Bake, uncovered, or cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Usually I boil skinned chicken pieces for about 2 hours to obtain broth. Then add other ingredients and you can also add any leftover vegetables like corn, okra, green beans, pinto beans. Bring broth to boil and then simmer for about 1 hour more.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Pour the melted bark over until it's coated well.
Drop by tablespoons on wax paper. Makes approximately 50.

title: balsamic peppered chicken
directions: On hard surface with meat mallet or similar flattening utensil, lightly pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Press lemon pepper seasoning evenly on both sides of chicken.
In large frypan, place oil and heat to medium temperature.
Add chicken and cook, turning once, about 7 minutes, or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Remove chicken to warm serving platter; keep warm.
In medium bowl, mix together the vinegar, broth and garlic; add to frypan.
Cook over medium-high heat, scraping up brown meat bits, about 2 minutes or until mixture is reduced and syrupy.
Add butter; stir to melt.
Place chicken on serving dish; spoon sauce over chicken.
Garnish with parsley sprigs and cherry tomatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable medley - on grill
directions: Cut tomatoes into cubes.
Cut peppers and onions into strips. Mix all vegetables and spices together, adding more amounts to taste.
Vegetables may be cooked in aluminum foil on the grill or a glass pan baked in oven.
If on the grill, place all contents in the foil (make foil large enough and close corners and top of foil to keep in heat).
Periodically stir the vegetables, and cook approximately 20 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Serve in a covered dish.
Serves 4.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix together.
Knead dough, roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
If hanger is desired, make sure to poke hole in top. Place in warm oven for 6 hours or overnight.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Pack cabbage in jars.
Add sugar and salt to each jar.
Cover cabbage with boiling water.
Seal.
Tops will come unsealed but will seal again.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple tidbits and mandarin orange sections.
In large bowl, combine cottage cheese, Cool Whip and dry Jell-O mix. Fold in pineapple and orange sections.
Chill overnight in refrigerator to blend flavors.
