title: seafood newburg
directions: Saute lobster, crab flakes and shrimp in 2 tablespoons butter with dash of paprika for a few minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon wine and toss over fire for a few minutes, then add 3/4 cup cream and bring to a boil.
Blend together beaten egg yolks and 1/4 cup cream and add to fish in the pan, stirring constantly, until thick.
Do not allow to boil.
Stir 1 tablespoon lemon juice, 2 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper into mixture and serve on toast, puff or in a chafing dish.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook beef with onion; add tomatoes, enchilada sauce, cumin, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour 1/2 meat sauce into casserole dish.
Spread tortillas with cream cheese.
Layer 4 tortillas on top of sauce. Sprinkle with green chilies.
Sprinkle with some of the Jack cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle top with Jack cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add half of the flour (3 1/4 cups), sugar, salt and shortening.
Blend at low speed with mixer, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Mix in remaining flour by hand. Cover and let rise until doubled (about 45 minutes).
Stir batter, beating hard about 30 seconds.
Spread in 2 greased loaf pans. Let rise about 20 minutes or until doubled.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: grandma quigley's hot rolls
directions: Take pan you are going to make rolls in and mix the sugar, shortening, salt and scalded milk.
In small bowl, put the yeast cake and lukewarm milk or water; let melt.
When lukewarm, put yeast and eggs; beat well in the pan.
Stir until it is ready to sift flour.
I usually sift 6 cups of flour.
Beat 1 cup at a time until ready to knead.
Knead, put in pan and grease top.
Let rise 1 hour.
Make into rolls.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: george strait's flour tortillas
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add just enough hot water to make a wet dough (not too light and not too stiff).
Shape dough into small meat ball size rolls.
On a floured surface, roll the balls very thin (about 1/8-inch thick).
Cook on hot skillet, brushed with vegetable oil, turning to brown both sides.

title: fancy pancakes
directions: Melt butter in cast-iron skillet.
Mix rest of ingredients; pour into skillet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Top with your favorite preserves and syrup.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Boil chicken breasts whole for 20 minutes.
Cool; cut into pieces.
Mix all ingredients, except stuffing and butter.
Spread mixture into a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix butter and stuffing; spread evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce walnut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove to rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Place potatoes in bottom of casserole dish.
Add onion, beans, rice, celery and ground beef.
Cover with tomato soup.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, eggs, white sugar, brown sugar, baking soda and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Butter a baking dish.
Layer potatoes, onion, peppers and ham, ending with a layer of potatoes.
Beat egg with milk and season to taste.
Add to casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Sprinkle with cheese and place under broiler until brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mamie's million dollar fudge
directions: Mix evaporated milk, sugar, butter and salt in a saucepan and bring to boiling.
Stir and boil for 7 minutes.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Pour boiling evaporated milk mixture over all.
Beat until fudge is creamy. Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch square pan to cool.
Cut into squares when cold.
Makes 30 squares.

title: rhubarb rumbell
directions: Microwave rhubarb for 6 to 8 minutes with cover on.
Stir. Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool completely.
Combine milk and pudding in mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer (hand one OK) for 2 minutes on low speed.
Fold in rhubarb mix.
Spoon in crust. Cover; refrigerate until firm.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Combine Minute rice, cooked meat, tomatoes, chopped onion, water, salt and pepper.
Cut green peppers lengthwise.
Fill with rice mixture.
Place in skillet with tomatoes around the peppers (I use 1 quart tomatoes, 1 cup in filling and the remainder in skillet).
Cover and cook 20 minutes or until peppers are tender. Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli.
Warm soup with cheese to melt; mix with rice and broccoli.
Place in buttered baking dish; cover with bread crumbs and a little melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients except kidney beans.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add kidney beans and cook until boiling.
Follow same procedure with crock-pot combining all ingredients, cook on high 5 or 6 hours or low 10 to 12 hours.

title: party fruit freeze
directions: Gradually add mayonnaise to cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add drained fruit and food coloring.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and freeze until firm.

title: lemon meltaways
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and confectioners sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in lemon juice. Combine the flour and cornstarch; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Shape into two 8-inch rolls; wrap each roll in plastic wrap. Refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm. Unwrap & cut into 1/4 inch slices. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350 degrees for 8-12 minutes or until the cookies are firm to the touch. Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Melt butter and sugar. Add egg. Add flour, nuts and vanilla. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except herb stuffing.
Place in casserole and cover with herb stuffing.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly and slightly brown. Serves 10 to 12.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour stuffed cabbage
directions: Use large outside leaves of cabbage.
Place in boiling water 5 minutes to soften.
Combine meat, rice, egg, salt, pepper and half the raisins.
Put a generous amount on each leaf; fold in sides. Roll up and fasten with wooden picks.
Shred the heart of cabbage.
Line bottom of heavy kettle with shredded cabbage.
Put stuffed cabbage on top.
Add remaining shredded cabbage, onion, raisins, lemon juice, sugar, tomatoes and water.
Simmer gently for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: sheila's cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into ball and coat with paprika. This is delicious.

title: reunion scalloped potatoes(serves 20)
directions: Arrange potatoes in buttered baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add egg yolks one at a time, beat after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add to mixture.
Add extract and lemon peel.

title: iams barbecue ribs
directions: Cut ribs into manageable portions.
Place olive oil in hot pan.
Saute green onions and garlic.

title: spaghetti loaf
directions: Mix lightly with hands and put into loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, mayonnaise and water in a bowl.
Add green pepper, onion, almonds and celery.
Mix well.
Cut chicken breasts into small pieces and add to mixture.
Mash hard-boiled eggs up and add this to mixture.
Mix well and put into large casserole dish. Crush potato chips in bag and add these to the top of the casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add honey; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine 3 cups flour, baking powder, salt, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon cloves and 1/8 teaspoon ginger; add to creamed mixture alternately with water, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat well after each addition.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to recipe or package directions. In a large bowl, toss apples with sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, lemon juice and seasonings until well coated.
Spoon into pie shell.
In small bowl, combine 1/2 cup flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Place pie in large brown, heavy-duty paper bag.
Fold open end over twice.
Seal with large paper clips.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until topping is golden brown.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and egg; shape into 4 patties.
Cook patties over medium heat, turning occasionally, until brown, about 10 minutes; drain.
Add onion, broth and mushrooms.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is done.
Remove patties; keep warm.

title: delicious chicken casserole
directions: Mix all; top with crushed cereal.
Spray oil in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ginger beer(native drink of st. croix, usvi)
directions: Wash and drain ginger.
Grind ginger in a meat grinder.
Pour water over ginger.
Steep overnight.
Strain through a clean, grease-free cheesecloth.
Add sugar and lime juice.
Pour into sterile bottles.
Serve chilled or pour over ice.
Makes approximately 2 quarts.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread the dry, uncooked rice in the pan.
Cover with chicken parts.
Pour the mushroom soup over chicken, then the can of water.
Sprinkle with the onion soup mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
You may add sauteed mushrooms and/or onions with the chicken if you wish.

title: orange smoothie(usa)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix until smooth and ice cubes are crushed.

title: deep sea pesto pasta(portuguese)
directions: In a medium skillet, heat the oil. Saute the garlic for 1 to 2 minutes. Add red, yellow and green peppers.
Saute 2 minutes. Add wine and seafood; saute for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in a casserole.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Add mashed bananas.
Add buttermilk and soda mixture alternately with flour into the mixture.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes in a greased and floured loaf pan.

title: glazed green beans
directions: Heat oil in iron skillet.
Add all other ingredients and cook on high until beans are glazed.
Turn down heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal quickies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to rolling boil and boil 1 minute.
Stir in oats, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts. Drop on wax paper with teaspoon.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in small saucepan. Gradually stir in hot water.
Stir and cook 3 - 4 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat only until hot.
Serves 12.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt butter. Add vegetables and saute on low. Stir in flour and cornstarch and cook until thick. Gradually add milk and chicken broth, stirring with whisk. Add soda and cheese. Stir until cheese is melted on medium heat. Add seasonings and cook on low heat for 10 minutes. Top with paprika.

title: great grilled burgers
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain well, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Cook onion in drippings until tender, but not brown.
Remove onion from skillet with slotted spoon and drain well.
In a medium bowl, combine catsup, horseradish, mustard, onion and bacon.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into six 3/4-inch patties.
Grill to desired doneness.
Serve on lettuce-lined buns.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Beat together sugar, oleo, egg and milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mix and beat until well mixed (will be thin).
Prepare two 8-inch cake pans (grease and wax paper). Spread mixture evenly into pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Brush with melted oleo.
Shake powdered sugar and cinnamon on top.

title: baked fruit with sour cream
directions: Drain the first 4 fruits.
(Reserve 1/2 cup of juice from one of the fruits.)
Arrange fruits in a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish.
Lay contents of 2 boxes of strawberries in center of fruits, butt side by side.
Sprinkle fruit with 1 cup brown sugar.
Add juice and rum.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve warm topped with sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Cook onion in melted butter in skillet. Brown meat; add spices and tomatoes. Cook 3 minutes. Spoon cooked macaroni into baking dish. Spoon meat mixture over the macaroni, together with tomato sauce and cheese. Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake 30 minutes.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and pack into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french toast
directions: In a shallow dish, beat together eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon until well blended. Heat a buttered skillet (1 tablespoon butter) over medium heat until just hot enough to sizzle a drop of water. One slice at a time, drop bread in egg mixture. Place bread in hot pan. Cook on both sides about 4 minutes on each side or until brown and no eggs remain.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter. Over medium heat, bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop on waxed paper. Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: sweetened condensed milk #1
directions: Combine powdered milk, sugar and warm water, mixing thoroughly.

title: pepper steak
directions: Put flank steak in Tupperware after grain is scored.
Put the rest of the ingredients over steak.
Turn a couple of times. Marinate overnight.
Broil a few minutes on each side.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Combine beef, onion, celery and pepper in skillet and cook until meat is light brown.
Add 2 cans green beans or English peas (if desired) and can of cream of tomato soup.
Simmer 5 minutes. Salt and pepper as desired.
Pour into lightly greased casserole; top with mounds of cream potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook sliced zucchini in salted boiling water for 5 minutes. Drain.
Add grated carrots.
Mix in sour cream and season.
Prepare stuffing according to directions.
In a well-buttered casserole, cover bottom and sides with moist stuffing.
Add filling and cover top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° until filling bubbles.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix first 3 and let boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 cups of cold water.
Mix; put in refrigerator until begins to jell good.
Add 2 cups shredded cheese and 1 (8 ounce) carton of Cool Whip.
Mix well and put back in refrigerator to jell.

title: jean's mess
directions: In large pot, brown meat, onion and garlic.
Drain excess fat.
Add soups, one at a time (no water or milk).
Cook on low heat for 45 minutes, or until bubbly.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking. Serve over Chinese noodles, egg noodles, or rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: In mixer bowl, slightly beat eggs; add sugar, corn syrup, butter, salt and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add pecans and pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 400°
oven for 10 minutes.
Decrease temperature to 350°
and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry-twinkie dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise in half; place cut side down in large 13 x 2-inch pan, Pyrex or Tupperware.
Mix the cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar; spread over Twinkies.
Combine glaze and strawberries; spread over top.
Cool.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peach crumb
directions: Empty can of peaches in baking dish.
Sprinkle entire cake mix on top of peaches.
Do not mix or stir!
Pour melted butter evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: red chili
directions: Brown steak in hot oil in a Dutch oven.
Add flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add water and remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Yields about 4 cups.

title: zesty deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise into halves.
Slip out yolks; mash with fork.
Mix in salt, mustard, pepper, mayo, cheese and parsley or horseradish.
Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it lightly.
Arrange eggs on large serving plate.
Cover and refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.
Each egg half can be garnished with cooked shrimp, rolled anchovy fillet or sliced pimento-stuffed olive before serving.

title: sauce for chipped ham
directions: Pour boiling water over other ingredients and mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat it in the oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg, beat; just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes, cool 3 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: italian drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add
eggs
and beat well. Add flour with baking powder and
salt.
Add 1 cup of milk and vanilla.
Add
pecans.
Drop
by spoonful and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: eggplant and rice fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into 1/2-inch hot oil in skillet.
Fry until brown.
(Fry amount needed to serve and refrigerate the rest.)
Will keep 3 or 4 days.

title: pizza porcupine patties
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Reserve 1 cup of the tomato sauce.
Mix remaining sauce, the ground beef, rice, chilies, salt, garlic salt and oregano.
Shape into 6 patties (1/2-inch thick).
Place in ungreased baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Remove patties from oven; drain.
Dissolve instant bouillon in boiling water; stir in reserved tomato sauce.
Pour tomato sauce mixture over patties.
Cover and bake 35 minutes. Spoon tomato sauce over patties; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: three bean hot dish
directions: Cook bacon, onion and hamburger in a pan on stove, stirring to break up meat until brown.
Drain.
Place in crock-pot.
Add beans, salt and pepper and mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl; mix well and add to meat mixture.
Mix until blended.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Combine meat, tomato juice, onion, seasonings and 6 cups water in soup kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Cut meat from bones in large cubes; strain broth and skim off excess fat.
Add meat and vegetables; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: pronto pups
directions: Boil franks for 15 minutes.
Dry with paper towel.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add egg and milk and beat until smooth.
Dip franks in batter and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: lemon fruited pudding
directions: Drain fruit, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 3 c.	Combine pudding mix, sugar and 1/4 c. water in saucepan. Blend in egg yolks and measured liquid.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, add fruit.
Chill.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Makes about 4 1/2 c. or 8 or 9 servings.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Beat cream cheese with mixer until well creamed.
Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy, about 3 to 5 minutes. Put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of regular-sized muffin cup (foil baking cups).
Pour batter into cups, filling 3/4 full.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tops are slightly brown.
Let stay in open oven for a while.
Cool. Refrigerate.
Top with pie filling.
Makes 18.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add water slowly.
Cook over medium heat beating constantly until it starts to boil.
Add 3 beaten egg yolks and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice, lemon rind and butter.
Cool.
Pour in 8-inch pie crust.
Make meringue and pour over pie filling.
Bake until done.

title: always ready bran muffins
directions: Combine 1 cup bran and 1 cup hot water.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat eggs slightly.
Combine all ingredients thoroughly and cover tightly in plastic container.
Let stand a minimum of 12 hours before baking.
Batter will keep in refrigerator for at least 6 weeks.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake in muffin tins for 18 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In large pot, place the chicken with skin removed, add diced tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover with water, bring to a boil, cook slowly until done.
Remove chicken from liquid, de-bone and cut into pieces.
Cook spaghetti in the liquid from the chicken; return chicken to pot.
In skillet, melt margarine, saute the vegetables.
Add mushrooms and olives.
Add all this to chicken mixture and lastly, add grated cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.

title: sticky nut rolls
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with oil.
Put broken nuts on bottom of pan.
Put the 18 frozen buns on top of nuts.
Mix together pudding, brown sugar and white sugar; put on top of rolls.
Melt margarine; pour on top.
Put Saran Wrap over pan and let set on counter top 8 hours or overnight.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pie (frisch's)
directions: Measure sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Add 1 cup water, stirring constantly. Bring to boiling point; boil gently 5 minutes to cook cornstarch. Cool slightly 10 minutes. Color to desired shade of red.

title: chili pizza
directions: Partially mash kidney beans with fork. Cook bacon until crisp. Remove from pan. Drain bacon grease. In the same skillet, brown ground beef and drain. Add picante sauce, beans and cumin. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring frequently, 10 to 12 minutes or until thickened.
Place pizza crust on pizza pan. Spoon meat mixture onto crust. Sprinkle with bacon and half the cheese.
Top evenly with peppers. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: nancy's chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken lightly.
Roll in flour.
Melt butter in large casserole.
Place chicken in butter and heat oven to 425°.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered.
Turn and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: christmas yule log
directions: Beat the egg whites with the salt until they stand in soft peaks.
Add 4 tablespoons of the sugar, one tablespoon at a time, and continue beating until meringue is very stiff.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg yolks with the remaining sugar and vanilla. Sift together the flour and cocoa.
Gently fold about 1/4 of the meringue into the egg yolk mixture.
Then pour back into the bowl of meringue.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of the flour-cocoa mixture and fold together.
Repeat until all the flour is blended. Be careful not to overmix.
Pour into a buttered 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan that has been lined with buttered wax paper.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400° until cake springs back at a touch. Sprinkle a tea towel with confectioners sugar.
As soon as the cake has baked, take it out of the oven and invert on the towel, so the waxed paper is on top.
Do not remove wax paper.
Roll the cake tightly in the towel to a 16-inch long cylinder.
Cool; carefully unroll and peel off the wax paper.
Trim off the crusty edges and spread the cake thinly with Butter Cream, then thickly with the whipped cream mixture.
Re-roll and refrigerate for half an hour.

title: chicken curry
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into lightly greased casserole dish (covered).
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Serve over cooked white or yellow rice.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: shake and bake mix for chicken
directions: Shake in bag to mix.
Two cups of mix is enough for 4 (3 1/2 pound) chickens.
Use 1/2 cup for 1 cut-up chicken.
Arrange in lightly greased pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes, turning once.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut steak into 1-inch cubes.
Brown meat slowly in skillet sprayed with Pam.
Transfer to 1 1/2-quart casserole with tight fitting cover.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer or until tender.
Serve on toast, rice or noodles.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Tear chicken into bite size pieces.
Add all ingredients to large crock-pot.
Simmer on low for 10 hours.

title: strawberry party punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool.
In large punch bowl, combine gelatin mixture, lemonade concentrate, orange juice concentrate and cold water; refrigerate.
Just before serving, gently stir in ginger ale and frozen strawberries.
Yields 28 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: slop over cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Put melted butter in a cup, add egg and add milk until it slops over the top of the cup.
Add to dry ingredients and beat well.
Turn into 2 greased 8-inch pans and bake at 375° to 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add oil, water and pie mix.
Beat well and add eggs one at a time.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Yields a large loaf and 6 mini loaves or a dozen muffins and 2 large loaves.
Adjust baking times for mini loaves and muffins.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Bring to a hard-boil stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, vanilla extract, chocolate chips and pecans.
Beat until chocolate loses its gloss. Pour into greased pan.

title: apple crescent rolls
directions: Open rolls and break apart at seams.
Peel and core apples. Cut into as many slices as there are rolls.
Place one slice on each roll; then place in a shallow pan.

title: charlotte elliot's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes, then cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Add margarine or butter, teriyaki sauce, garlic salt, Italian seasoning and the red and black pepper.
Toss to combine.
Cover; microcook on High for 12 to 15 minutes (14 to 16 minutes for low-wattage ovens), or until potatoes are tender, stirring twice during cooking.
Stir before serving.
Garnish with rosemary.
Makes 5 side dish servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together well the first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well together.
Mix carrots, pineapple and nuts together.
Bake at 350°.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add to first 4 ingredients.
Marinade overnight.
Add tomatoes shortly before serving.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Combine oats, flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Spread cranberry sauce in bottom of 9-inch pie plate or tin.
Sprinkle other mixed ingredients over cranberry sauce.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: salmon vegetable loaf
directions: Mix salmon and vegetables all together with salt and pepper. Then fold in egg whites. Put in baking dish and pour tomato sauce over it. Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cream shortening and margarine together to a liquid form.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add water and stir in completely. Chill in fridge until a nice handling compound.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with sage, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and melted chocolate.
Add flour and baking soda.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Take chips and nuts and spread in bottom of unbaked shallow pie shells.
Beat the rest of ingredients together and pour over nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Coat over medium heat.
Stir about 3 to 5 minutes.
Knead on a lightly floured surface.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chip nut pie
directions: Melt the butter and let cool.
Beat eggs by hand until frothy. Add the sugar, flour, butter and vanilla; mix well by hand only. Add the chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix.
Pour into pie shells and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown and solid in center.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add syrup, sugar, vanilla, salt and butter.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: friendship cake(abbreviated version)
directions: Drain peaches, pineapple and fruit cocktail, reserving juice for other uses; halve cherries.
Combine fruits.

title: cherry pecan pudding
directions: Combine sugar, egg and pecans.
Add dry ingredients, alternately, with milk.
Fold in cherries.
Pour batter into 8 inch pan and bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with sauce.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, topping with Rice Krispies.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.
This is great served with croissants or rolls for a luncheon.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Oreos.
Layer creamed mixture and cookies, ending with cookies on top.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut off tips of broccoli; drain.
Peel, wash and dice the onion.
Add raisins.
Crumble up bacon.
All of these ingredients should be in a large bowl.
Marinate 24 hours in mixture of mayonnaise, white vinegar and sugar.
Mix and pour over salad.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in greased baking dish.
Top each chicken with Swiss cheese.
Mix together soup and milk, and pour over chicken and cheese.
Top evenly with green pepper.
Combine stuffing mix and butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until juices run clear.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° until light brown. Remove from cookie sheet at once with spatula. Keep mixture stirred before dropping on cookie sheet so all the milk won't go to the bottom.
They may run on cookie sheet, but they will shape up into balls when removed while hot. (You may add more dates and cherries.
Also, red and green maraschino cherries are pretty for Christmas.)

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in top of double boiler or in microwave.
Stir during melting process.
Pour noodles and nuts into melted butterscotch.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple juice until moist.
Add Cool Whip and the pineapple to the pudding mix.
Chill.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix; put in graham
crust and refrigerate.
Will make 2 medium sized pies.

title: honey bear brownies
directions: Cream margarine or butter and sugar in small mixer bowl. Blend in honey and vanilla.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost with creamy brownie frosting.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken in cool water; dry thoroughly.
Beat egg with water.
Combine cracker meal with seasonings.
Dip chicken pieces first in egg mixture, then in seasoned cracker meal.
Place butter in large, shallow pan.
Place in preheated hot oven at 400° until melted and lightly browned.
Place chicken pieces, skin side down, in melted fat.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 30 minutes more.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop and steam all vegetables until just tender.
Boil last 5 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add hot vegetables to hot juice and let stand about 12 hours.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: sweet potatoes with pineapple
directions: Boil potatoes; slice into pieces.
Place a layer of sweet potatoes in a buttered casserole.
Cover with a layer of pineapple slices.
Repeat layers to top.
Sprinkle top of casserole with remaining ingredients.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Great with ham, but good with barbecue for a change.

title: kahlua chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, eggs, sour cream, kahlua and vegetable oil.
Beat at low speed to blend, and then on medium-high for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
(I use cocoa rather than flour so that the cake doesn't have white flour on the outside).
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until done. Cool in pan on rack for 30 minutes; remove from pan to completely cool on rack.
Dust cake with powdered sugar, if you wish.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix together hamburger, oats, onion, eggs, oregano, salt, basil and tomato sauce.
Form into loaf.
For sauce, combine catsup, brown sugar, soy sauce, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Place meat loaf in Dutch oven and pour sauce over it.
Bake until done, about 1 hour with 4 to 8 coals under the oven, 12 to 18 on top.

title: rainbow angel cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package.
Add lemon peel.
Divide batter evenly in 3 bowls.
Fold 1 color in each bowl of batter. Pour green in ungreased tube pan, spread evenly.
Repeat with yellow and red.
Bake and cool as directed.

title: nine bean soup
directions: *To make mix:
Combine 1 pound each of Great Northern, pinto, red, black, black-eyed peas, lentil, barley, navy (small white) and split peas.
Mix together and put 2 cups in jar.
Makes 10 pints.

title: baked potato soup
directions: In a large soup pot, melt butter.
Add flour and stir until thick.
Add milk to mixture; stir and cook until thickened.
Add Velveeta and potatoes.
Season with other ingredients.
To serve, place soup in a bowl and top with bacon and chives.

title: pig picken cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges in a large bowl. Blend on low speed for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour 2 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 33 to 38 minutes.
Mix pudding mix with 1 1/2 cups milk until thick.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add pineapple and whipped topping to pudding; blend well.
When cake has cooled, poke holes with a toothpick and pour reserved pineapple juice evenly over layers.
Frost with the pudding mixture.
Top cake with pecans, if desired.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per package.
Cook chicken.
Mix everything together, omitting enough cheese for top.
Place mixture in baking dish.
Top with croutons and cheese mixed with melted butter. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells and bake at 275° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken strata
directions: Cut the bread into 1-inch cubes and place on the bottom of a 12 x 18-inch nonstick pan.
Combine the chicken, onion, celery, chilies, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in a medium bowl; spoon over bread cubes.
Tear the tortillas into bite size pieces and place on top of the chicken mixture.
Combine the eggs, milk, cottage cheese and soup; pour over the top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to allow the flavors to blend.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Heat together vinegar, pepper, salt, sugar and oil until dissolved; set aside to cool.
Place vegetables in
a large container and pour dressing over vegetable mixture and refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: low-fat pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine pasta, broccoli and carrots.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, garlic, Italian seasoning, pepper and mustard.
Pour over salad and toss to coat well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix together corned beef, cheese, milk, soup and onion.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add noodles, after cooked, to corned beef mixture.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top mixture with shredded bread. Melt oleo and pour over bread crumbs.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until cheese bubbles.
Uncover and brown bread crumbs just a few seconds.

title: apple oatmeal coffee cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl. Add remaining ingredients and stir; mixture will be thick. Pour into greased 8 x 8 pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 9.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream with butter.
Add beaten eggs, then milk.
Cook in a double boiler until thick and smooth.
Pour into pie crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potato chip casserole
directions: Mix hamburger, soup, milk and peas and carrots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
For the last 5 minutes of baking, cover top with potato chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: If raisins are used, pour a cup of boiling water over raisins. Let stand until raisins are plump, drain and use mix according to list.
Bake in 350° oven until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Pick peas.
Shell and wash.
Put in pot.
Add salt and meat. Cover with water.
Cook until peas are tender.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until brown.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together lightly by tossing with a fork.
Beat egg well; add the water and the vinegar and mix all together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until moist.
Mold together with your hands; don't handle too much at once.
Chill before rolling.
Can be kept in refrigerator for 1 week.
You can freeze this crust also.

title: chili-chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
In large skillet, cook and stir onion in butter until tender; stir in soup, pimiento and chili pepper.

title: company rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, but not browned.
Combine rest of ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix well.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer. Serves 4.

title: pastiche(greek)
directions: Brown the hamburg.
Saute the onion and simmer together for a short time.
Add salt, pepper, cinnamon and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Cook the macaroni.
Strain macaroni and add a little butter to keep from sticking.
Melt butter.
Add flour and milk; heat.
Beat 12 eggs well and fold into milk.
Add the cheese. Add egg and milk mixture to macaroni.
Fold in.
Put layer of macaroni mixture on bottom of large 11 x 16-inch pan.
Add hamburg mixture on top and end with top layer.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, then at 300° for 1/2 hour or golden on top.
Preparation time:
30 minutes.
Total cooking time:
1 hour.

title: ma's choco fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt in a cooking pot.
Add milk.
Boil until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until mixture thickens.
Pour into square baking pan.
Let cool in refrigerator. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve.

title: simple pralines candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk, salt and butter in a pot.
Stir over medium heat, stirring until all sugar is dissolved.
Cook until soft ball stage and then remove it from heat.
Add vanilla and beat until this is creamy and smooth.
Next, stir in nuts and drop onto wax paper.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix ingredients together in crock-pot and heat for 2 hours, stirring occasionally to dissolve red hots.

title: brown sugar chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together
first
5 ingredients.
Mix flour, salt, sugar and soda together.
Add to sugar mixture gradually.
Mix in chips and
nuts.
Drop
by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at
for
minutes
for chewy cookies, 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: sweet and sour sandwiches
directions: Cook sugar, eggs and juice of lemons together in double boiler or thick pot until thick.
Add mayonnaise while hot, then add raisins and nuts.
Make one big loaf whole wheat bread.

title: st. patrick's day punch
directions: Combine Jell-O and 2 cups boiling water.
Stir until well blended.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill several hours before serving.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs and bananas.
Combine milk and lemon juice.
Add.
The add dry ingredients.
Blend well. Stir in walnuts.
Grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 60-70 minutes until bread looks done in cracks on top.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Chill until set.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute onion in butter until golden. Blend in flour and seasonings; cook until bubbly. Remove from heat; add milk gradually. Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute (stir constantly). Remove from heat again and add corn and egg. Place in baking dish. Top with buttered crumbs. Bake for 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: ashley catchapaw's mushroom splendor
directions: Dice or slice mushrooms.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cool in frypan until tender and heated through.
Add Italian dressing to above mixture and serve over meat.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water, cornstarch and salt; cook until clear. Remove from heat.
Add food coloring and strawberry jello to mixture.
Stir well; cool.
Place strawberries into baked pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries; cool.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: molasses corn balls(this is very good!)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add molasses and sugar.
Bring to boiling and let boil until mixture becomes brittle when dropped into cold water, stirring constantly.
Gradually pour over popped corn, which has been sprinkled with salt.
Shape into balls, using as little pressure as possible.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, stir together sugar, salt and milk, mixing well.
Add chocolate and butter.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Stir well.
Microwave on Medium-high for 14 to 15 minutes, uncovered.
Stir well every 5 minutes.
When done mixture should form a soft ball in cold water or register 235° on a candy thermometer.
Let candy stand, without stirring, at room temperature until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat with spoon until mixture thickens and loses its gloss.
Quickly stir in the nutmeats and pour into wax paper lined 8 x 4-inch loaf dish.
Cut when set.
Yield:
makes 1 pound.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with 1 whole onion until potatoes are done. Discard onion.
Mash potatoes with cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
If dry, add a little milk and 1 beaten egg. Refrigerate in buttered dish.
Dot with butter on top. Cover while refrigerated.
Bring to room temperature.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Beat milk, oleo and sugar until smooth; add eggs which have been beaten slightly.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and cinnamon. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: classic beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat diagonally into very thin strips.
Cook and stir mushrooms and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Remove from skillet.
In same skillet, brown meat lightly on both sides.
Set aside 1/3 cup bouillon.
Stir remaining bouillon, catsup, garlic and salt into skillet.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
Blend reserved 1/3 cup bouillon and flour; stir into skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Add milk to thin to desired consistency.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread bean mixture in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed: avocado dip, sour cream, ripe olives, tomatoes, onion and Monterey Jack cheese.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes about 15 to 20 appetizers.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Put in crock-pot and cover with 2-inches of water.
Cook for several hours.
Serve over rice.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Put peas and 8 cups or more water into a covered pot and bring peas to a boil over high heat, then reduce to simmer about 45 minutes or until tender.
While peas are cooking, cut meat into cubes and dice onion. Put in skillet and fry 5 minutes, until crisp.
When peas are done combine meat, onions, rice, thyme, red pepper and peas and stir.
Simmer another 25 minutes until rice is done and liquid is absorbed.

title: molded cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add mayonnaise or salad dressing and beat with rotary beater or electric mixer until smooth.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in cottage cheese, celery, pepper and onion.
Pour into 4-cup mold and chill until firm.
Unmold onto a lettuce-lined serving plate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a heavy saucepan boil the potatoes until done.
Drain; allow to cool.
Remove skins.
In mixing bowl, grate potatoes; add onion, sour cream, butter, 2 cups cheese, salt and pepper. Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish; top with 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Press cookie dough onto pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until brown.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine pudding mix with milk and almond extract in bowl; beat well.
Spread over baked crust. Chill in refrigerator until set.
Top with fruit.
Cut in wedges to serve.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: soldier boy cookies
directions: Roll thin.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Roll pin over lightly.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Just try them.

title: edible necklace
directions: Thread needle with string.
Alternate candy, macaroni, marshmallows and licorice pieces on the string until necklace is filled.
Tie ends of string.

title: karo v i p pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling together, adding pecans last. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 400° oven 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
When pecan pie is done, outer edges of filling should be set, center slightly soft.

title: mexican corn bread bake
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook for several minutes, stirring frequently.
Add salt, seasoning mix and tomato sauce.
Spoon into baking dish.
Spread mixture of corn muffin mix and evaporated milk over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar and eggs.
Sift together baking powder, salt and flour; add to cream mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine the sugar, flour, baking soda, cocoa and salt and sift into an 8-inch square pan.
Make 3 holes in the sifted dry ingredients.
Into the 3 holes, add the salad oil, vanilla and the white vinegar.
Lastly, add the 1 cup of cold water over all and stir with a fork until well blended.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add melted margarine and egg. Slowly stir in milk until mixture is of batter consistency.
Heat a small amount of oil in a flat skillet.
Make sure skillet is covered.
Pour batter into skillet to make pancakes in size desired.
Serve warm with your favorite toppings.

title: corned beef dip(reuben)
directions: Melt butter.
Add beaten egg, sauerkraut, corned beef and cheese.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Can be used cold as a regular dip or put on cocktail rye bread and baked for approximately 15 minutes at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.
In punch bowl, crumble a layer of cake.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip, a layer of pudding and a layer of strawberries.
Start again: crumbled cake, Cool Whip, crushed pineapple, pudding mix, strawberries, etc.
Top with Cool Whip, garnish with sliced strawberries and then sprinkle crushed pecans. Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in pecans and morsels.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon (a little less if you want smaller cookies) onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in hot oven at 400°.
Turn oven off at once; don't open oven door until oven is cold.
Keep in airtight container.
Will keep several weeks.
Do not refrigerate.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and chop fruits. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add lemonade concentrate and stir until melted. Chill until slightly thickened. Blend in Cool Whip and fold in fruit.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours. Unmold and slice. Makes 12 servings.

title: old-time egg custard pie
directions: Blend eggs and sugar; add salt and flavoring.
Slowly add scalded milk, while stirring.
Pour into pastry lined 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until firm.
It will set some more as it cools.

title: dump delight
directions: Spread pie filling and pineapple in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit (do not stir). Top with nuts and coconut.
Pour melted butter over all and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Serve cool with whipped topping.
Serves 15.

title: ninann salad
directions: Cook on low heat the sugar and pineapple and juice.
Dissolve lemon jello and hot water.
Combine all of this and let set until medium firm.
Take whipped cream and mix with pimento cheese. Then add this to the jello and pineapple.
Let set.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it crackles in cold water, then add salt, peanuts and butter.
Cook and stir until syrup browns lightly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda; stir and pour in 2 heaps on buttered containers.
I use pizza pans to pour candy on.
Measure all ingredients in advance.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix in order given, beating butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla, beating until light.
Beat, beat, beat.

title: skillet summer squash
directions: Saute onion and peppers.
Stir in sugar, flour, butter, salt and pepper.
Add squash and tomatoes.
Cook until tender.

title: angel food cake dessert(no bake; delicious)
directions: Slice cake 1-inch thick and pack tightly into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Top with prepared jello (do not jell).
Top with peaches. Top with instant pudding.
Top with sliced bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Top with crushed peanuts and maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into prepared pan.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy brownie pie
directions: Melt together unsweetened chocolate and butter in microwave or saucepan.
Add sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May be served with ice cream.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Grease a loaf pan.
Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients, then bananas, nuts and sour cream.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green peppers
directions: Stew in tightly covered pot approximately 30 minutes.
(Add no water.)

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Slice chilis and remove fiber and seeds.
Layer chilis, then both cheeses. repeat layers.
Final layer should be cheese.
Blend eggs, flour and evaporated milk.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes. remove from oven and pour tomato sauce over casserole. Add a layer of both cheeses and bake uncovered for 15 minutes. Serves 6-8.

title: german chocolate bars
directions: In a bowl, mix the cake mix, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and melted butter.
Pour half of the batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Place in bread tin that has been greased. Top off with slices of cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry glazed baked apples
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar, juice and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until apples are tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining sugar.

title: date cake squares(diabetic)
directions: Combine water, dates, prunes and raisins in medium saucepan. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until fruit is tender and water is absorbed, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add margarine, stirring until melted. Cool to room temperature.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil hen until done.
(I have used chicken pieces, legs, thighs, breast to equal 5 pound hen.)
Reserve broth.

Saute celery, onion, mushrooms and bell pepper in 2 tablespoons butter. In a large pan make a sauce of 2 tablespoons butter, flour and milk and add cheese (cut in small pieces) and stir until cheese melts. Add sauteed onion, celery, pepper and mushrooms.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and add to sauce.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
When spaghetti is done, drain all but one cup broth and add sauce to mixture.
Put into casserole (1 large or 2 medium).
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding.
Add a little green cake coloring, then add the balance of ingredients.
Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch strips and lightly salt.
Mix 1/2 teaspoon salt and the pepper with 1/4 cup flour.
Dredge meat and brown in hot oil.
Set aside remaining seasoned flour.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add tomato liquid, water, beef stock base, onion and garlic to the meat in skillet.
Cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Add green pepper strips and Lea & Perrins and simmer 5 minutes more.
Blend in tomatoes and reserved flour and simmer about 5 minutes.
Delicious with noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue pig feets
directions: Wash pig feets, season to taste.
Let set 30 minutes in seasoning with vinegar.
Cook feet until done, add hot sauce and more vinegar, ketchup and barbecue sauce.
Let it cook down to a simmer.
Serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Spray large Pyrex pan (9 x 13-inches) with oil.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: golden wassail
directions: Pour juices into 20-cup electric percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in basket.
Allow to go through cycle.
Serve hot. Makes 20 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: sausage and rice ole
directions: Thinly slice smoked sausage and place in a large skillet with onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute over medium heat until onion and bell pepper are tender.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomato paste, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Place rice in a large casserole dish.
Pour sausage and tomato mixture over rice; stir together.
Top with cheeses and olives.
Place in a 350° oven until cheese melts and casserole becomes bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not substitute ingredients, or it will not taste the same.

title: grannys jambalaya
directions: In a large pot melt Crisco; add flour stirring until golden brown.
Add onion, pepper and celery; saute vegetables for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add tomato puree,
tomatoes, seasonings, and water to vegetables; simmer for one hour.
Twenty to thirty minutes before serving add shrimp and simmer for five to ten minutes; then add instant rice.
Turn off stove and let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: venison stew
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil.
Add horseradish, onion soup mix, tomato juice, mushroom gravy and water.
Simmer 1 hour. Add more water to make as much liquid as before; bring to a boil. Add vegetables.
Turn down the heat and simmer until vegetables are done.
Thicken with cornstarch, if desired.
Serve with hot butter.

title: swiss cheese enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken breasts; skin, debone and chop them coarsely.
In skillet, saute onions in butter.
Add chopped chicken, olives, sour cream, cream cheese, green chilies, 1/2 of the cheeses and the chicken soup.
Assemble the tortillas in a greased baking dish as follows:
Steam to make them pliable and fill the center with the chicken-cheese mixture.
Roll and place in baking dish with the seam down.
When the pan is full, sprinkle remaining cheeses over the top.
Cover with foil; bake for 30 minutes at 350°, or until bubbly.
Makes approximately 12 enchiladas.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain and set aside. In a skillet, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, mustard and salt.
Heat until bubbly.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, arrange half of broccoli and top with half of eggs, half of cheese and half of mushroom soup.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle onions on top and bake 5 minutes more. Yields 6 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put 1 layer of asparagus in casserole.	Top with 1 egg, sliced, and 1/2 the cheese and chestnuts.
Repeat layer.
Pour undiluted soup
over
all.	Put a few cheese squares over top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: herb dip
directions: Mix all together. Cool.
Use for vegetables as hors d'oeuvres.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour and pineapple juice together and cook until thickened.
Cool overnight.
Next day, whip whipping cream and fold pudding into cream.
Add oranges, pineapple, grapes, bananas, apples and walnuts to pudding mixture and enjoy.

title: chocolate mint cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box, adding creme de menthe.
Then bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely.

title: jiffy brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat and eat.

title: marinated artichoke hearts
directions: Put artichokes in pint jar with lid.
Mix other ingredients and pour over artichokes.
Rotate jar to keep artichokes moistened.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 days before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together soda, cinnamon, salt and flour.
Put diced apples in large bowl.
Add sugar, oil and nuts; mix well.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: cranberry jelled salad
directions: Drain liquid from pineapple reserving juice (should be 1 cup of juice). Put juice in saucepan and bring to boil. Remove from heat and add cherry Jell-O. Dissolve well. Add the can of whole cranberry sauce and mix well. Add pineapple, celery and nuts (optional). Pour into serving dish or Jell-O mold. Chill until set.

title: potato casserole
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into dish.
Mix bread crumbs (1/2 package seasoned stuffing mix) and 1/2 stick margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in large bowl.
Add crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges, drained.
Add Cool Whip, then add jello.
Mix; let set several hours.

title: kasutera cake(angel food cake)
directions: In one bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat at least 12 minutes at fastest speed of mixer.
(If using Kitchen Aid mixer, beat at #7.)
Add 1 cup cake flour (Softasilk) to mixture; beat well.

title: honey fried chicken with warm blue cheese slaw
directions: Mix together honey and buttermilk.
Marinate chicken overnight.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Heat oil to 325°.
Remove chicken from marinade and dredge through seasoned flour.
Fry in oil for 8 to 10 minutes, depending on size of chicken.
Serve on top of Blue Cheese Slaw.

title: rainbow poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as on package.
Pour batter into 2 round pans, 8 or 9-inches.
Bake as directed.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix together.
Add cheese mixture to crepe.
Fold one side then the other.
Add sauce, then sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or microwave.

title: pickled zucchini
directions: Let stand covered in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: carbonade of beef
directions: Heat butter and oil to sizzling.
Brown the beef.
Reduce heat and brown onions.
Season with salt and pepper and stir in the garlic.
Layer the beef and onions in a casserole.
Pour in beer and stock.
Stir in the sugar.
Add the bouquet garni.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites with a mixer until stiff.
Add the other ingredients by folding gently in.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Turn oven off and put cookies in. Forget them.
They are ready to eat in a few hours.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Slice cooked chicken against grain in 1/4-inch thick slices. In large bowl, combine chicken, scallions and half the cheese. Add cumin to taste.
Place mixture onto each tortilla and roll up. Place in ungreased baking pan, seam side down.
Pour enchilada sauce over all.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: paul bunyan sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in milk and raisins.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir until well blended.
Chill one hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into well-greased, hot iron frying pan.
Cook in a preheated 400° oven for approximately 30 minutes, or until done.

title: cheesy apricot dip
directions: Simmer apricots in 1 cup water.
Cover for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
In processor or blender, combine apricots with liquid and sugar, blend until smooth.
Add cheese, sour cream and nutmeg.
Blend until smooth. Cover and chill.

title: top of the stove cookies
directions: Boil for 1 minute, milk, sugar and oleo.
Mix peanut butter, oatmeal, cocoa and vanilla.
Add to boiled mixture and stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: mushroom stuffing
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove with a slotted spoon to paper towels.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings. Saute celery and onion in the drippings until tender.
Add mushrooms, sage, salt and pepper; saute for 5 minutes.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in stuffing, celery leaves, parsley and bacon; mix well.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°. Stuff the chicken breasts and tie with kitchen string.
Brush the outside of the breasts with the oil which has been blended with paprika and, optionally, 1 teaspoon salt.
Place in a shallow casserole.
Place stemmed while grapes around fowl.
Bake about 35 minutes, until delicately browned.
Brush with oil and baste frequently (at least 3 times) with orange juice or mixture.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit together.
Mix pudding and pineapple juice.
Pour over fruit.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Put 2 quarts water in medium saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Add a pinch of salt (vegetable oil, optional) and noodles.
Continue boiling about 12 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Brown ground beef and drain off excess fat.
Mix spaghetti sauce and ground beef and pour over noodles.

title: pilaf
directions: Brown noodles and rice in butter.
Add next 5 ingredients to the noodle and rice mixture.
Cook in covered pot for 20 minutes. Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes longer.
Remove cover, mix lightly and continue cooking 10 minutes longer on low heat.
tags: cream of chicken soup or chicken broth

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in oven; bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Put back in oven; let brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook white Karo syrup and water until it spins, then add peanuts and sugar.
Stir until they pop good.
Then add vanilla and soda.
Then you stir like crazy. Put in a margarine greased pan.
Do not smooth or shake.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine first four ingredients and freeze.
When ready to use, thaw couple of hours.
Pour in ginger ale.
I always make 2 recipes.
Freeze a month ahead if need to.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt.
Cover with chopped ice for 3 hours; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers and bring to a boil.
Pour into jars.
This is good on hot dogs or hamburger sandwiches!

title: "talerene"
directions: Brown onion in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Add hamburger meat, mushroom soup, corn and tomato juice.
Next, add cooked noodles and hot pepper sauce.
Salt to taste.
Spread in casserole dish with part of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add remaining cheese on top.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Put sugar, vinegar and oil in small pan and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and pour over kraut, peppers, celery and onions.
Mix thoroughly and place in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in the order given.
Add a handful of chopped nuts and raisins if desired.
Put into two well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until done.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Add taco seasoning and water according to the package.
In large bowl, add hamburg, kidney beans, taco sauce and Catalina dressing.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients plus any you prefer.

title: sweet potatoes with garlic in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread each foil sheet with a little margarine.
Divide sweet potatoes, garlic and tarragon equally on the foil pieces and dot with the remaining margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2 inch baking dish. Top with cheese slices. Combine soup and milk; stir well. Spoon sauce over chicken and sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter over crumbs. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: sour cream crumb coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with mixture of sour cream and vanilla.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Pour half the batter into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle half the topping mixture over it.
Cover with rest of batter, then sprinkle with remaining topping.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix together the graham crackers, butter and sugar. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and set a couple of minutes.

title: quick orange yogurt coffee cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine egg and yogurt; add cake mix.
Stir until well combined.
Stir in raisins.
Pour batter into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In small bowl, stir together the sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over batter in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool on wire rack. Makes one coffee cake.

title: toasted cheese sandwiches
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Cut crust off of bread. Spread on one slice, top with second slice.
Cut in quarters.
Do this until all bread is used.
Then ice top and sides of each square with cheese spread.
Top with 1/2 inch square of bacon. Tray freeze.
Bake in top of oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Broil thereafter if necessary.

title: microwave no fuss caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn and peanuts in large brown paper bag and set aside.

title: quick skillet cornbread
directions: Grease skillet and heat.
Pour in skillet.
Bake at 400° about 10 to 15 minutes.
It's best to use an iron skillet.

title: calico casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare macaroni and cheese.
Use milk. Add peas and soup.
Mix well; pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole. Slice Spam diagonally and arrange around edge of dish; bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat and pour into pie crust.
Top with the other crust.
Bake until the crust is brown and done.

title: chocolate skillet pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Slightly beat yolks and add milk. Melt margarine in heavy skillet.
Stir in sugar mixture until well blended.
Remove from heat and add egg and milk mixture.
Return to heat and stir until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla and pour into crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar, one at a time, and cream of tartar.
Spread over chocolate.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in large saucepan and add water to cover.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer over medium heat until tender, then drain.
Place potatoes in mixer bowl.
Cut butter and cheese into small pieces and add to potatoes.
Beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat in sour cream.
Season with nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Serve immediately or reheat in a buttered casserole at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: hungarian cabbage rolls
directions: Mix meat, egg, onion, rice in a bowl, salt and pepper to taste.
Cut around core of cabbage and remove it.
Put cabbage in large pan of boiling water.
Cook a few minutes until leaves can be removed.
Remove leaves 1 at a time.
Do not use very small leaves.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries into graham cracker crust.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O and water until thick.
Pour over strawberries in crust.
Cool; refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemony.
Add sugar gradually.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients together and fold in mixture gradually by hand.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread 1 cup peanut butter over cake while still hot.
Allow to cool and add melted 8 ounce Hershey chocolate bar.
Spread evenly over cake.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Put 1 1/2 inches oil in skillet.
Flour and salt chicken.
Then put in pot with barbecue sauce and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Saute margarine, onions, green pepper and celery.
Cook rice. Add Cheez Whiz, soup and broccoli.
Top with cheese; bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Very good family favorite.
Can be made in 2 dishes; freeze one.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with cream.
Add flavoring.
Pour into a tube pan that has been sprayed with Pam or greased and floured.
Place cake in a cold oven.
Set temperature at 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan.

title: rhoda's pasta salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: guacamole
directions: In a mixing bowl, wash the avocado with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Chill covered for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs, then add strawberries and lemon juice.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour and spices. Gradually stir dry ingredients into strawberry mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and pour batter into two greased loaf pans. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour in saucepan.
Add milk and egg yolks; mix well.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add butter; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Spread meringue over filling, sealing to edge.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: caramel cream cheese bonbons
directions: Combine caramels and milk in large bowl in microwave.
Heat until melted.
Stir in 1 cup powdered sugar, margarine and pecans. Cool to room temperature, then stir in cream cheese.
Add 1 pound or more powdered sugar until mixture can be made into balls after being chilled.
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll into balls and place on wax paper and freeze for 1/2 hour until firm.
Melt almond bark or chocolate and quickly dip bonbons in with toothpicks and place back on wax paper.
Return to refrigerator until coating is hard. Store in refrigerator.

title: high fiber snack
directions: Place oatmeal, coconut, walnuts, bran and salt into bowl; mix well.
Mix peanut butter and honey separately.
Combine the two mixtures.
Pack in pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: egg nog bread
directions: In a bowl, cream together egg, egg nog, oil and nuts.
In second bowl, sift together dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture. Stir well.
Place in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes a large loaf.

title: sugared asparagus
directions: In a skillet over medium-high heat, heat butter and brown sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add asparagus; saute for 2 minutes. Stir in chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until asparagus is crisp-tender.
Remove asparagus to serving dish and keep warm.
Cook sauce, uncovered, until reduced by half.
Pour over asparagus and serve immediately. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix well.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 300° very slowly until done.
Remember that all ovens do not heat the same.
Check heat and adjust if needed.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine garlic, mayonnaise, mustard and lemon juice in blender.
Pour over pasta.
Add rest of ingredients along with tomatoes, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and let stand for several hours or overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Mix egg, onion, bread crumbs, salt and pepper until bread crumbs are moist.
Add tuna and make into cakes.
Brown in hot skillet until done, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: creamy oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add oysters and cook over low heat until edges curl.
Slowly add the half and half and heat gently.
Do not boil.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve steaming hot with oyster crackers.
Seasoning is very important to this stew.
Salt and pepper should be added according to personal taste.
Flavor improves if allowed to stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Reheat gently.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: swedish tea logs
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, sugar and salt in bowl.
Cut in margarine.
Add milk, egg, raisins and yeast.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator, covered, from 2 hours to overnight. Cream 1/4 cup margarine.
Add brown sugar, creaming well.
Add nuts.

title: fruit, pudding salad
directions: Peel and slice bananas into chunks.
Put lemon juice or Fruit-Fresh on bananas to keep from turning dark.
Add pineapple with
juice and instant pudding to bananas.
Stir.	Drain peaches and
set
juice
aside.
Add
peaches
to other fruit mixture. Drain
mandarin
oranges
and
add to fruit mixture. Stir.	For thinner pudding, add some or all of peach juice.

title: pineapple chiffon pie
directions: Add enough orange juice
to juice from the pineapple to equal 1 1/2 cups of
liquid.
Bring
to
simmering point.
Add gelatin, stirring to dissolve.
Let
cool to room temperature. Combine cottage cheese, yogurt
and pineapple in blender.
Add extracts, lemon rind and puree
on
low
speed for one minute. Pour into cooled gelatin mixture and refrigerate until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat
egg
whites
until
firm.
Drop
1/3 beaten whites into cheese
mixture.
Blend
well
with
whisk. Pour balance of egg whites into mixture and fold gently.
Cool in refrigerator until almost set, about 45 minutes.
Turn into baked pie shell. Sprinkle
with chopped nuts and refrigerate. Allow two hours to set.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Use boneless, skinless chicken.
Brush each piece with safflower oil.
Dredge lightly in flour or bread crumbs.
Season with pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn.
Bake 10 to 25 minutes more or until tender.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain, then mix beans, tomatoes, tomato paste and chili powder.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell. Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook for approximately 1 hour.

title: sauce for pudding
directions: Mix and beat well. Cook in double boiler 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat muffin appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crabmeat, Swiss cheese and mayonnaise in bowl; add garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Spread on muffins.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake until cheese melts and top turns lightly brown, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut each muffin into four and serve while warm.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved, then cook, without stirring, to 260°.
Remove from heat and pour, beating constantly, in egg whites.
Add vanilla and continue beating until mixture holds its shape and becomes slightly dull.
Fold in nuts.

title: candied apples
directions: Boil mixture until it forms a hard crackling in water (candy thermometer reaches 300°).
Do not stir after sugar is dissolved. Dip apples in mixture.
Place apples on buttered plate.

title: 'schrooms(excellent mushrooms)
directions: Remove and chop mushroom stems.
Saute chopped stems and scallions in butter until tender (liquid should be absorbed). Remove from heat.
Combine cheese, mustard and Worcestershire. Add to mushroom mixture with meat.
Mix well.
