Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: b'stilla
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water, oil and butter.
Remove and shred chicken.
Bring broth to boil and scramble 6 eggs in boiling broth.
Grind almonds.

Add cinnamon and sugar (1 teaspoon each). Layer in buttered 13 x 9-inch dish, thawed filo dough (1 or 2 sheets), eggs, almonds, chicken, repeat eggs, almonds, chicken, then 2 or 3 sheets of filo dough on top.
Spread about 1/4 cup melted margarine over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
You may sprinkle additional powdered sugar after baking.
Yum!
Yum!

title: monkey bread
directions: Drop quartered biscuits into sugar and cinnamon.
Shake to coat well.
In saucepan, melt brown sugar and oleo.
Put biscuits into greased Bundt pan (or Pyrex bowl).
Pour melted mixture over coated biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: special baked beans
directions: Fry and cut bacon until almost crisp. Chop onion and cook 5 minutes. Drain kidney and butter beans. Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar and syrup together in 2 qt casserole.
Microwave on high 4 minutes, stir in peanuts.
Microwave on high 3-5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla, blend well and microwave on high 1-2 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Cool one hour and break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes approximately 1 lb.

title: green salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and pineapple juice. Add softened cream cheese and mix well (wire whip works good). Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat whipping cream and fold into Jell-O/cheese mixture.
Fold in crushed pineapple.
Chill until set.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add the jello. Cool to room temperature.
Fill baked crust with sliced berries. Pour cooled syrup over.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together into a large bowl.
Make a well in the center and add in the order given the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth. Stir in carrots, coconut, nuts and pineapple.
Blend until well blended.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cool completely and frost with cream cheese icing.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Keeps 1 month in refrigerator. Yields about 8 dozen.

title: apple cranberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine the cranberries, sugar, tapioca, water and orange peel.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in apples.
Set saucepan in a pan of cold water for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, line pie plate with the bottom pastry.
Pour filling into crust.
Top with remaining pastry or a lattice crust.
If using a full top crust, cut a few slits in it.
Beat egg white until foamy.
Brush over top pastry.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes or until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbly.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar and then add egg yolks. Pour in milk a little at a time until well mixed. Put on stove and stir until it is good and thick. Stir in butter. Pour into a ready bake crust. Let set until cool.

title: mission sangria
directions: Dissolve sugar in juice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add fresh oranges, mint, grapes for garnish and serve with ice.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Cook cake in 13 x 9-inch cake pan as directed.
While cake is baking, bring to a boil milk, sugar and 1/2 of coconut.
Pierce the cake with fork and pour hot mixture over it.
Chill.
Cover with Cool Whip and rest of coconut.
Refrigerate.
Delicious with vanilla ice cream or boiled custard.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake about 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: afternoon delight
directions: Make the German chocolate cake according to directions, but add the extra egg and oil.
Bake according to instructions. While cake is still hot, poke holes in the top of it with the handle of a wooden spoon.

title: gertrude's gingerbread
directions: Combine molasses, butter and sugar.
Add salt and spices; stir together.
Add egg and milk.
Sift together soda and flour, then add to mixture.
Pour into greased tin.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Lay chicken in baking dish and cover with dressing, soup mix and jam.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: strawberry or cherry pudding
directions: Grease and
flour
x
13-inch
pan.	I cut up strawberries or sour
cherries and put all over bottom of pan.
Run batter mixture all
over top of berries.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: punch
directions: Mix everything except ginger ale.
Refrigerate.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°. In medium saucepan, combine 6 ounces chocolate with butter, sugar and water. Cook over low heat, stirring, until melted. Set aside to cool. Break up remaining chocolate and stir into melted chocolate mixture. Whisk in eggs, flour and salt. Add walnuts, if desired. Batter will be thick and lumpy. Spray a 9-inch square pan with nonstick spray and spread mixture into pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Set on rack to cool. Garnish with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: angel hair pasta with shrimp
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Melt butter and oil in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add shrimp and garlic and cook for 6 minutes, stirring frequently, until shrimp are pink.
Using slotted spoon, remove shrimp and keep warm.
Add cream, wine, peas, parsley, 1/4 cup Parmesan, basil and red pepper to the skillet.
Blend well and bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add pasta and shrimp.
Toss until well mixed.
Serve immediately with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: sauerbraten(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Select meat with a layer of fat.
Cut off some fat and set aside.
Place meat and vegetables in a bowl with vinegar and enough water to cover.
Add bay leaves, peppercorns and cloves tied loosely in cheesecloth.
Cover and place in a cool place for 3 days.
Drain meat, reserving vegetables, liquid and spices. Sprinkle meat with flour, salt, pepper and allspice; brown on all sides with drippings from reserved fat.
Add the vegetables and about 2 cups of reserved liquid from meat.

title: bonfiglio's ice cream cake
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar.
Add flour.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into egg, sugar and flour mixture.
Pour in greased and floured cookie sheet pan with sides, approximately 11 x 17-inch.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from pan on a towel or rack and when cool, spread ice cream (softened) on cake.
Roll like a jelly roll; wrap and freeze. Serve frozen.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk in large saucepan.
Over low heat, bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes, stirring to avoid scorching.
Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously, making sure everything is dissolved.
Pour into greased 9 x 13--inch pan. Refrigerate until it gets hard.
Makes about 3 pounds of fudge.

title: very easiest - peach pie (fresh)
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half of mixture over unbaked crust.
Arrange peaches in single layer over mixture. Sprinkle with rest of sugar mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until juices thicken and crust is light brown.

title: no-flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Press with fork to crisscross.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Also you can use any kind of chips (chocolate, vanilla, etc.), mix in chips at beginning or add them fresh out of oven.

title: ham and pickle bites
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Spread over ham.
Place pickle on this and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Slice rolls into bite size pieces.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ham-vegetable chowder
directions: Combine tomato soup and water in a Dutch oven; add celery and onion.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add mixed vegetables.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes or until tender.
Add potato soup and remaining ingredients; bring just to a boil.
Yield:
7 cups.

title: quick scalloped potatoes
directions: Put chips in 1 1/2-quart or 2-quart baking dish with lid.
Add milk.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes covered.
Stir; bake 15 minutes more, uncovered.
Yield:
approximately 1 quart.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Crush corn flakes.
Drain 1/2 the liquid off salmon.
Combine all ingredients.
Spray loaf pan with nonstick spray.
Pour mixture in pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
For a firmer loaf, use 2 eggs and 1/4 cup oleo.

title: easy chicken main dish
directions: Brown chicken strips in electric skillet (sprayed with Pam) until browned.
After chicken strips are browned, add soup, milk, lemon juice and paprika.
Simmer covered for about 45 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: stove-top baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients into a frying pan and cook over medium heat until onion is done.

title: face paint
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Add vegetable dye to obtain desired coloring.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix and bake cake in 9 x 13 pan according to directions. Cool slightly. Poke holes in cake with handle of a wooden spoon. Drizzle condensed milk over cake. Refrigerate until cold. Spread on Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Butterfingers. Cover and store in the refrigerator.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Spread slices with butter.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and set aside.
Cook sausage until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Spoon over bread slices; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt.
Mix well and pour over cheese.
Cover casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake casserole uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash, drain and leave a 2-inch stem on beets. Cover with boiling water. Cook until tender. Peel. Combine all ingredients except for beets. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: can salad
directions: Open and drain cans.
Quarter the artichoke hearts.
Place all ingredients in a bowl and add the salad dressing. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Stir-fry chicken with a little salt until cooked.
Stir-fry vegetables.
Combine chicken, vegetables, cashews and cornstarch mixture with spices.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken saladwestboro, missouri
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then mix dressing together and combine with chicken.
Let chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Peel, cut up and cook squash in small amount of water (with salt, pepper and a little onion, if desired) until tender.
Drain well and lightly mash.
Generously cover bottom and sides of casserole with butter or oleo.
Press onto bottom and sides 1/2 package of stuffing.
To squash, add 1 can soup and sour cream. Mix well.
Put in casserole and cover with remaining stuffing. Melt 1 stick oleo and pour over topping.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water, let stand 5 minutes.
Drain. Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl beat sugar, shortening and eggs until fluffy.
Add flour mixture and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Frost.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cheese cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Butter 9-inch spring-form pan.
Mix butter and crumbs well.
Reserve 1/4 cup and press the remainder firmly on the bottom of the pan.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until foamy.
Gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar and beat until stiff.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix pumpkin, sugar, margarine and salt. Cook until done (precooked pumpkin is best and just bring to a boil).
Blend well the next 4 ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shells and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Cook until done.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until well done; then peel and mash.
In a mixing bowl mix potatoes, sugar, coconut extract, nutmeg, 1/2 stick margarine and cinnamon until smooth.

title: beef brasi - barbecued meat
directions: Pierce roast deeply all over with a fork.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large bowl; place roast in bowl, turning to coat well; cover.
Chill, turning meat several times, 2 days.
When ready to cook, remove roast from marinade, saving marinade in a small pan.
Place roast on spit. Set spit in position over hot coals; start rotisserie.
Roast and brush several times with marinade.
For rare meat, cook about 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot crimson apple punch
directions: In a large kettle, combine apple juice, cranberry juice cocktail, cinnamon	sticks	and cloves; bring to a simmer over medium-high flame.	Pour
into
a large punch bowl and stir in lemon
juice.
Garnish
with
orange
slices.
Yields
1/2 gallons.

title: pink punch
directions: Put sherbet, juice and pop in punch bowl.
Add 7-Up and ice cubes.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter.
Add cereal and stir.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper; or roll into balls.
Chill and serve.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Wash, drain and cool.
Combine with rest of ingredients and toss.
Let set overnight.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water. Set aside.
Mix flour, salt, sugar and milk.
Cook until warm.
Add beaten egg yolks. Continue cooking until thick. Remove from heat.
Add gelatine, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat egg whites stiff. Fold into custard.
Add the pineapple, thoroughly drained, to the custard before folding in egg whites.

title: alabama pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add half of the butter and enough milk to make like thin pancake batter.
Pour into pan.
Arrange peaches and lemon slices on top of batter.
Pour liquid from peaches over the top. Pour sugar over top.
Then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: wild rice-chicken soup
directions: Wash wild rice by placing in wire strainer.
Run cold water through it, lifting rice with fingers to clean thoroughly. Heat rice and chicken broth to boiling, stirring once or twice.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until tender, 40 to 50 minutes.
Cook and stir mushrooms, celery, onion, garlic, salt and pepper in margarine in 3-quart saucepan until celery is tender, about 6 minutes.
Stir in flour. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in cut up chicken and chicken broth with rice.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in cream and wine.
Heat just until hot (do not boil).

title: tim's stew
directions: Dredge meat in flour, salt and coarsely ground pepper.
Brown in 3 tablespoons lard or beef fat heated pan.
Add large onion and celery (diced).
After browned well, cover with water and simmer slowly 3 to 4 hours (in winter, simmer on top of wood stove).
One and one-half hours before serving, add diced carrots and potatoes. Serve with biscuits and salad.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Handle as little as possible.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Nice cookies to decorate.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Cut ham and cheese in small pieces about the size of roll. Use about 3 packages of ready to serve rolls of 24 to a package.

title: ale 8 cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; set aside.
Mix Ale 8, margarine and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour this mixture over the first mixture.
Mix eggs, buttermilk, soda, vanilla and marshmallows and first mixture together and bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cut up onions, green pepper and celery and fry in oil 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, Tabasco and vinegar. Simmer slowly for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Add cooked shrimp 15 minutes before serving.
Serve
with rice.

title: sausage cabbage skillet
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: beer chicken
directions: Saute chicken in salt-free butter with onion until light brown. Simmer on low for 10 minutes.
Pour beer and spices over chicken which is in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over chicken 1 minute before removing from oven.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Add butter after it boils and gets thick.
Put in cooked pie shell and make meringue.

title: snow balls
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons sugar, flour, butter and walnuts.
Roll into little balls.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Let cool. Put remaining sugar in paper bag.
Put in snow balls and shake for coating.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: arlene's taffy
directions: Cook until a small amount dropped into cold water cracks. Pour into a greased pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: orange slice bars(gumdrops)
directions: Cut orange slices in small pieces with scissors dipped in cold water.
Add flour and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread in two greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut in 1 x 3-inch bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook the broccoli until tender.
Drain and arrange on a flat, flameproof dish.
Melt the butter and stir in the flour. Add the milk and cook, stirring constantly, until the sauce is thickened and smooth. Add the bouillon and stir to dissolve.
Pour half of the sauce over the broccoli. Top with the chicken and cover with the remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Put the dish in the broiler or 375° oven until the cheese is melted and the sauce is bubbling hot.

title: vinegar taffy(an old, old recipe)
directions: Boil to hard-ball stage.
Pour in buttered pan.
Cool until you can handle it.
Rub hands with butter before pulling.
It will turn a beautiful creamy white.
Cut into pieces and wrap individually with foil or wax paper.
Store in airtight can.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Add water to frozen juices, using package directions.
Combine juice mixtures and pineapple juice in freezer container.
Mix well.
Freeze.
Combine juice mixture and club soda in punch bowl 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.
Garnish with sliced oranges.

title: clam sauce
directions: Saute celery, mushrooms and garlic in olive oil.
Add liquid from clams and shrimp.
Add tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Heat; add clams and shrimp.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: butterscotch apple slices
directions: Line tray with waxed paper. Wash apple. Dry thoroughly. Remove core and cut apple into 8 slices.
Blot dry with paper towels.
Place butterscotch chips and 2 teaspoons shortening in a medium bowl and microwave on High for 30 seconds until chips are melted when stirred. With fork, dip each slice completely into mixture.
Tap fork and gently shake to remove excess.
Place slices on prepared tray.
In a small bowl, melt chocolate chips with remaining shortening on High in microwave for 15 seconds. With tines of a clean fork, drizzle chocolate over tops of the apples.
Makes 8 coated apple slices.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookies according to package directions and cover an ungreased pizza pan with them.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°; cool. Add sugar and vanilla to softened cream cheese.
Spread on baked cookies.
Drain pineapple and oranges, reserving juice.
Put fruit in decorative rows on top of cream cheese mixture.
Add tapioca to reserved juices; cook until slightly thickened.
Cool and pour over fruit as a light glaze.

title: holiday fruit punch
directions: Combine sugar in small amount of water (2 cups).
Stir until dissolved.
Add balance of water, juices and tea.
Mix well and pour over ice cubes in punch bowl.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix chopped dates, baking soda and boiling water. Allow to cool.

In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients. Add date mixture. mix with wooden spoon. Add beaten egg and butter, mix. Stir in chopped nuts. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until sugar is dissolved.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add vanilla and flour.
Add cream last.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix together marshmallows and peanuts or pecans.
Set aside.
On low heat, melt together milk, chocolate chips and butter.
(Can be melted in microwave.) Pour over marshmallows and nut mixture.
Mix well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish (or a dish lined with wax paper).
Place in refrigerator.
When it is cool, cut into squares.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round baking pans.
In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or more.
Cool cake for 10 minutes and layer cake with whipped cream (2 cups).

title: marinade for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken and marinate for two hours or overnight.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter and oats.
Spread 1/2 of crumb mixture in bottom of greased 8-inch square pan. Pour in pie filling.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: quick chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add cheese sauce.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add chicken soup, chicken and pimento. Pour into casserole and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Bring 1 gallon of water to boil and add potatoes. Cook until knife pierces easily into potato, about 30 minutes. Cool completely. Peel and cut into 1-inch cubes in large bowl. Add bell pepper, celery, green onions, mayonnaise, garlic powder, white pepper, seasoning salt and black pepper. Mix well. Makes 6 servings.

title: another squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with Ritz crackers.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: granny's prune cake
directions: Sift the flour and measure. Re-sift twice with the spices and salt.

Add the prunes, sugar, oil and eggs; mix thoroughly all ingredients except pecans with electric mixer. Fold in pecans by hand. Turn into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Check for doneness after 1 hour and 20 minutes. Turn onto cake rack and cool. Ice with a powdered sugar glaze icing.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and bake 2 1/2 hours in slow oven at 350°.
Set in pan of water, if possible, after first hour.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Remove from heat; blend in flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk and heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens a little and is smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese and heat until melted, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Combine with sauce in 2 quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese, bread crumbs and paprika. Bake at 375° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Cream peanut butter and margarine.
Stir in vanilla and salt. Add sugar gradually (little can milk).

title: congealed green salad
directions: Make jello.
When thickened, add other ingredients.

title: peaches and cream cheese pie
directions: Mix flour, salt, vanilla pudding, egg and milk together in a blender or mixer.
Pour into greased 9-inch or 10-inch deep dish pie plate.
Drain large can (about 30 ounces) sliced peaches, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Arrange peach slices over flour mixture.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 3 tablespoons peach juice together until smooth (2 minutes).
Spoon over peaches and batter to within an inch of edge of dish.
Mix together 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve at room temperature.

title: italian green beans
directions: Combine.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip or dressing for salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind the vegetables with the coarse blade of meat grinder. Place the vegetables in a stainless steel kettle; cover them with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and add vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Boil for 25 minutes.
Pack the vegetables in sterilized pint jars.
Pour the hot liquid over the vegetables, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Seal and process for 10 minutes in a hot water bath according to the water bath instructions in a quick dill pickle recipe.

title: zucchini puffs
directions: Drain zucchini for a while.
You can use apples instead of zucchini.
To apples, add cinnamon, sugar or nutmeg to your taste. Use the hole grater not the fine one.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Set oven to 325°.
Pour milk over bread cubes.
Add salt and sugar.
Beat eggs; add with butter and vanilla to mixture.
Mix well after adding raisins.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Set dish in a pan; pour hot water to within 1-inch of top of casserole.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: hot toddy
directions: In an 8-ounce mug, place sugar syrup, cinnamon and your choice of whiskey, rum or brandy.
Fill mug with hot water.
Impale over edge of mug the lemon slice, studded with cloves.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute celery and onion in butter.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Add other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf supreme
directions: Combine mayonnaise, soup, egg, green pepper and lemon juice. Mix well and add salmon and bread crumbs.
Bake in greased 8-inch loaf pan for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large bowl except marshmallows. Pour into casserole dish. Top with marshmallows.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: shell-less coconut custard
directions: Put all ingredients, except coconut, in blender or food processor on low.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken parts and place in casserole.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: grape-nuts pie
directions: Let Grape-Nuts and warm water stand until water is absorbed. Add Grape-Nuts to egg mixture and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until filling is puffy completely across top.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Make a well in the center and stir in the buttermilk until soft, but not sticky.
Turn out onto a floured board and form into a patty 6 to 8-inches in diameter.
With a sharp knife, cut crisscross 1/2-inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden.
Cool before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pink lemonade sherbet punch
directions: Mix together well the chilled ingredients, adding last the scoops of sherbet to float on top.
This amount makes a punch bowl full to rim.

title: chocolate mounds candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together into bite-size balls.
Chill. Melt chocolate chips with 1/2 block cake paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Grease shallow serving platter (13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch) glass baking dish.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix cake mix and dry yeast together.
In separate bowl, mix water and salt until salt dissolves.
Add to first mix slowly, then work in flour.
Knead good.
Turn upside-down in bowl. Grease top and let rise.
Then make into rolls and let rise again. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
well.
Grease
and
flour 2 loaf pans. Pour in pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in olive oil in a large saucepan; add tomatoes, tomato paste, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles in a large amount of boiling, salted water for 15 minutes.
Drain and lay in single layers until dry.

title: velveeta cheese dip
directions: Heat the cubed cheese and milk in a heavy pan to melt cheese. Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir constantly over heat with cheese and milk.
Serve cold for dip with tortilla chips or warmed over cauliflower.

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in half and half and chicken broth.
Stir constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Combine sauce with cooked rice, chopped pimiento and parsley, chicken and almonds.
Pour into 2-quart casserole which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until thick.
Pour into 2 baked crusts.

title: green beans with herb butter
directions: Cut beans into thin slices.
Cook beans, covered in 1/2-inch boiling salted water for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Or use a 16 ounce can cut green beans, drained.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop up and combine tomatoes, onions, green and red peppers. Put salt over them and leave in a plastic container overnight. Drain in
the morning.
Combine celery seed, vinegar and sugar. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Place in hot pint jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: chicken and wine casserole
directions: Boil chicken, celery, onion, salt and pepper until chicken is cooked.
Put chicken (without skin) in casserole dish.
Spoon out celery and onion over chicken.
Put cheese on top and then mushroom soup over.
Cover with bread cubes.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and spoon over bread.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: african yams
directions: In a covered skillet, cook yams in 3 T margarine and water over low heat until tender.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: no-cook ice cream
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs gradually and beat until very stiff. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put in ice cream freezer. Work the freezer as usual or use an electric freezer as directed.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, flour and sugar.
Add boiling water gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes on the surface unit on high heat.
Add butter, egg yolks, rind and juice of lemon.
Turn switch off.
Blend thoroughly.
Cook until thick. Pour in baked shell and cool.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix syrup and sugar in a 1 or 2 quart saucepan.
Heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour cereal into a large bowl.
Stir peanut butter mixture into cereal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let it cool.
Eat and enjoy.

title: tea punch
directions: Get a pan, cheese and 2 pieces of bread and butter.
Set oven for 350°, use the top of the stove; let the pan warm and put some butter in. Let it melt and put the sandwich in the pan.
Wait until the bread gets brown and use a spatula to flip the sandwich. Wait until the other side gets brown.
Take the sandwich out and put it on a plate and eat it.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns for 30 minutes.
Combine all but last 2 ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased casserole dish. Combine corn flakes and margarine.
Spread on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: trail cookies
directions: Stir flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter, peanut butter and sugars until creamy.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, then oats, chocolate and raisins.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Peel carrots and grate coarsely.
Add raisins.
Mix mayo, honey and vinegar.
Add cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour over carrots. Chill at least 2 hours or longer.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook 20 minutes.
Put in hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Bake chicken breasts in slow oven until done.
Season with salt, paprika, celery leaves, onion and sliced carrots.
Debone while hot.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Add chopped hard-boiled eggs, chopped celery, slivered almonds, celery salt, chopped onions (if desired) and Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Mix well and chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg.
Mix together flour and soda and add it to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate approximately 6 hours or overnight, if desired.
Makes into small rolls or loaves before placing in refrigerator.

title: mom's homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add Pet milk, sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in fruit.
Freeze until electric freezer stops.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Cream shortening or butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: garden pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Separate into rectangles.
Spread on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Press edges and perforations to seal.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in salted water until stems are almost tender. Drain and put in ungreased casserole.
Mix soup and milk
and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: pie crust(four single crust)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients with pastry blender until pea size.
Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Form into a big ball.
Separate into 4 equal smaller balls.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling.
Will keep in refrigerator a week or it can be frozen.

title: colorado superbowl chicken hero sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken, mayonnaise, tomatoes with juice, mustard, 1/2 green onions, chestnuts, Worcestershire and 1 cup cheese.
Slice French loaf in half and place on cookie sheet. Spread chicken mixture over bread and bake 10 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with 1 cup cheese and remaining green onions.
Bake another 10 minutes.
Perfect with chips and salsa.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Place all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening.
Beat until well mixed. Add egg and buttermilk.
Beat just until barely moistened. Spray muffin tins with Pam or use paper cupcake liners.
Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes. Let set in pan 2 minutes before removing.
Serve hot with butter and honey.

title: seafood linguine
directions: Cook linguine according to package; drain.
Melt butter in frypan, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer while linguine is cooking.
Then combine and mix all ingredients.
Serve.

title: zesty salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well except Tabasco.
Add a few drops to taste.

title: strawberry chantilly
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin and water in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil and is clear.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package and thoroughly blend into chilled pudding mixture.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Top with strawberries.
Makes 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: southern fruit pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Add all dry ingredients except 3 3/4 to 4 cups flour to large mixing bowl.
Add water and oil that has been heated to 120° to 130°; mix well.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Add enough of the 3 3/4 to 4 cups of flour to make a smooth dough, but not sticky.
Mix well; knead dough for about 7 minutes.
Grease large bowl; place dough in bowl, turning once to grease both sides of dough.
Cover; let dough double in size.
Punch down; knead dough with hand for about 1 minute, then turn onto floured surface.
Roll out; cut with biscuit cutter and dip half of roll into melted butter.
Fold over; pinch shut and place on greased baking dish.
Cover.
Let raise until doubled, about 50 minutes.
Bake in oven at 375° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken breasts with marsala wine
directions: Beat eggs with salt and pepper.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken breasts in eggs, then coat with bread crumb mixture.
Let coated chicken stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt butter with oil in a large, heavy skillet.
When butter foams, add chicken breasts.
Cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until chicken has a light, golden crust. Add Marsala wine.
Cover skillet and reduce heat.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
If sauce looks too dry, add a little more wine.
Turn chicken several times during cooking.
Place chicken on a warm platter.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Serves 8.

title: garlicky roast potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes for 10 minutes at 400°.
Place potato wedges (skin side down) in baking dish.
Season, scatter garlic and dot with butter.
Roast 30 minutes, until well browned.
Turn to insure even roasting.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in hot fat and drain.
Add sauerkraut, then brown sugar, potatoes and onion on top.
Salt and pepper potatoes, then add hot water.
Bring to a boil and turn down heat to low. Put tight lid on and cook for about 45 minutes.
Serve with cornbread.

title: zeppolis(with ricotta)
directions: Mix well (very sticky dough).
Drop by scooping with hands into hot oil.
Zeppolis will rise to top.
When golden brown remove from oil and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Eat hot.
. .mmmm better than St.
Anthony's feast!

title: company casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup, curry and parsley with fork and place in buttered casserole dish.
Place the pieces of chicken on top of mixture.
Sprinkle dry onion mix on top.
Bake covered for 2 hours at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, milk and salt in a saucepan.
Cook and stir on medium heat until thick.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix jelly and chili sauce together in pot on stove.
Jelly will melt.
Round meat balls, putting a piece of water chestnut in each one.
Put on pan and bake at 375° to 400° until done, then place in sauce.

title: pinwheels
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and dressing mix until smooth.
Add red peppers, celery, onions and olives; mix well. Spread on each tortilla.
Roll up tightly.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Slice in to 1/2 inch pieces. Yield 15 - 20 servings.

title: anne's shrimp butter
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese together.
Add onion, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Stir in shrimp.
Chill.
Serve with crackers. Can be frozen.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix in the following order:
sugar, flour, salt, egg, water, butter, vinegar, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fried apple rings
directions: Core apples and cut each in 4 circles.
Melt fat in a frypan. Add sugar and lemon juice (if used).
Add apple slices and cook slowly about 10 to 15 minutes until tender.
Turn as needed to brown.
Makes 4 servings.
Another light and healthy dessert.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain well.
Beat together eggs, cream cheese and cream of mushroom soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add broccoli.

title: marshmal-o fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and Marshmallow Creme.
Boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour into buttered dish.
Chill.
Makes 2 1/4 pounds.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine sugar, water and butter in pan.
Cook to 300°, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Add vanilla and pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Lay the 4 chocolate bars on top and spread evenly as they melt.
While still warm, sprinkle chopped pecans over top.
Cool completely and break into pieces.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: country captain chicken
directions: In medium saucepan, saute onions, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in 2 teaspoons salt, pepper, curry powder and thyme.
Simmer 5 minutes; set aside.

title: northern style corn bread
directions: Toss dry ingredients to mix.
Beat eggs; add milk and butter. Then add to the dry ingredients and stir just until moistened. Pour batter into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven about 30 to 35 minutes or until browned and center comes out clean when tested with a toothpick or knife.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup of the sugar.
Melt butter in the dish you will use to bake your cobbler.	Blend remaining cup of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over the melted butter. Do not stir.
Put peaches on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until crust is golden brown.
They will rise during baking.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil for 3 full minutes.
Take from stove and add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Boil water and butter; add flour, stirring fast until dough forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each egg.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Watch closely. Cool.

title: blush fruit dip
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh array of fruits.

title: grilled turkey breast
directions: Combine everything but the meat to make a marinade sauce. Marinate the meat in the refrigerator for several hours (minimum). Put on the grill and enjoy!

title: taco salad
directions: Combine cheese, tomato sauce, garlic and chili powder.
Lay aside.
In a large bowl, combine lettuce and chopped tomatoes. Add Tostitos, hamburger meat and onions.
Pour cheese sauce over lettuce and tossed mixture just before serving and toss.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: honeyed chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Beat eggs with tablespoon of water. Mix matzo meal, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg, then in matzo meal.
Brown in hot oil.
Remove to Dutch oven or covered roaster.
Mix hot water, orange juice and honey.
Pour over chicken.
Cover.
Simmer on top of stove or in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until tender.
Baste frequently.

title: ham salad(salad bowl puff)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inch.
Heat water and margarine to boiling in 2-quart saucepan.
Add baking mix, all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time; continue beating until smooth. Spread in pie plate (do not spread up side).
Bake until puffed and dry in center, 35 to 40 minutes; cool.
Just before serving, fill with Ham Salad Filling.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: key club pie
directions: Blend the milk with lime juice, grated lime rind and egg yolks in a bowl.
Pour into the graham cracker crust.
Beat the egg whites and cream of tartar in a bowl until foamy.
Add the sugar gradually and beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread over filling, sealing to edge of crust.
Bake at 425° for about 4 minutes or until brown.

title: boneless chicken and peaches
directions: In a saucepan reduce wine by 1/2 and remove it from heat.
Add preserves and Worcestershire sauce and let cool.
Arrange chicken and peaches in a glass baking dish.
Top with preserve mixture and marinate overnight.
Sprinkle brown sugar over the top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar, eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Mix well. Add coconut.
Pour into two 8-inch pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: million dollar lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce in small pieces.
Using a 9 x 11-inch dish or pan, arrange in layers:
lettuce, onion, celery, chestnuts, peas and mayonnaise, sprinkled with sugar.
Cheese goes on top of final layer.
Cover pan with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. When ready to serve, you may wish to top this dish with tomato wedges, crumbled bacon and/or hard-boiled eggs (sliced).
Mix salad together just before serving.

title: garlic fried chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Place chicken in a shallow pan and pour buttermilk mixture over top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
Remove chicken from liquid.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Heat 1-inch oil in a large skillet to 325°.
Add chicken and fry 30 to 35 minutes, turning once.
Drain chicken well on paper towels.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: polish spaghetti
directions: Brown onion and kraut in oleo.
Mix with other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover top with foil, not too tight.

title: glorified gingerbread
directions: Blend the following with pie crust blender until fine: flour, shortening, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Save 1/2 cup for later use. Add soda, ginger, egg, molasses and sour milk; mix well and place in greased square baking pan.
Spread the 1/2 cup dry mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: toll house mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and vanilla until creamy; add egg and beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Spread in foil lined 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 23 to 25 minutes. Immediately sprinkle 2/3 cup chocolate chips over top.
When morsels are shiny, spread evenly.
Chill to set chocolate.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Makes 36 bars.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients except cheese and pour into 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake for about 45 minutes; put cheese on top and bake another 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: ginger ale molded fruit salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water. Dissolve in boiling fruit juice. Add lemon juice, ginger ale and sugar. Chill until almost set. Add canned pineapple and fresh fruit.
Put in a wet mold to chill.

title: peanut butter loaf
directions: Mix all and bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: summer sunshine salad
directions: Combine jello, tapioca pudding and boiling water.
Refrigerate and stir every 2 hours.
Add pineapple, oranges and Cool Whip.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain, crumble and reserve.
Add onion and green pepper to bacon drippings and saute until tender.
Add rest of ingredients, except shrimp, and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
When ready to serve, add shrimp and simmer about 10 minutes.
Do not overcook; serve over white rice and sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
